  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: "Introduction to Moses\u2019 First Address"
      content: '  These are the words that Moses spoke to all the people of Israel
        while they were in the wilderness east of the Jordan River. They were camped
        in the Jordan Valley[[COMMENT(0)]] near Suph, between Paran on one side and
        Tophel, Laban, Hazeroth, and Di-zahab on the other.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Arabah; </b>also in 1:7.
    - title: 
      content: 'Normally it takes only eleven days to travel from Mount Sinai[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to Kadesh-barnea, going by way of Mount Seir. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Horeb, </b>another name for Sinai; also in 1:6, 19.
    - title: 
      content: 'But forty years after the Israelites left Egypt, on the first day
        of the eleventh month,[[COMMENT(0)]] Moses addressed the people of Israel,
        telling them everything the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded him
        to say. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>In the fortieth year, on the first day of the eleventh
          month. </b>This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in January
          or February.
    - title: 
      content: 'This took place after he had defeated King Sihon of the Amorites,
        who ruled in Heshbon, and at Edrei had defeated King Og of Bashan, who ruled
        in Ashtaroth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Command to Leave Sinai
      content: "While the Israelites were in the land of Moab east of the Jordan
        River, Moses carefully explained the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s instructions
        as follows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen we were at Mount Sinai, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God said to us, \u2018You have stayed at this mountain long enough. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is time to break camp and move on. Go to the hill country of the
        Amorites and to all the neighboring regions\u2014the Jordan Valley, the hill
        country, the western foothills,[[COMMENT(0)]] the Negev, and the coastal
        plain. Go to the land of the Canaanites and to Lebanon, and all the way to
        the great Euphrates River. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Shephelah.</b>
    - title: Moses Appoints Leaders from Each Tribe
      content: "Look, I am giving all this land to you! Go in and occupy it, for
        it is the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to give to your ancestors
        Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and to all their descendants.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses continued, \u201CAt that time I told you, \u2018You are too
        great a burden for me to carry all by myself. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has increased your population,
        making you as numerous as the stars! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of your ancestors,
        multiply you a thousand times more and bless you as he promised! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you are such a heavy load to carry! How can I deal with all your
        problems and bickering? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Choose some well-respected men from each tribe who are known for
        their wisdom and understanding, and I will appoint them as your leaders.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen you responded, \u2018Your plan is a good one.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I took the wise and respected men you had selected from your tribes
        and appointed them to serve as judges and officials over you. Some were responsible
        for a thousand people, some for a hundred, some for fifty, and some for ten.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAt that time I instructed the judges, \u2018You must hear the
        cases of your fellow Israelites and the foreigners living among you. Be perfectly
        fair in your decisions "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and impartial in your judgments. Hear the cases of those who are
        poor as well as those who are rich. Don\u2019t be afraid of anyone\u2019s
        anger, for the decision you make is God\u2019s decision. Bring me any cases
        that are too difficult for you, and I will handle them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: Scouts Explore the Land
      content: "\u201CAt that time I gave you instructions about everything you were
        to do.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God commanded
        us, we left Mount Sinai and traveled through the great and terrifying wilderness,
        as you yourselves remember, and headed toward the hill country of the Amorites.
        When we arrived at Kadesh-barnea, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I said to you, \u2018You have now reached the hill country of the
        Amorites that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God is giving us. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look! He has placed the land in front of you. Go and occupy it as
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of your ancestors, has promised
        you. Don\u2019t be afraid! Don\u2019t be discouraged!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you all came to me and said, \u2018First, let\u2019s send
        out scouts to explore the land for us. They will advise us on the best route
        to take and which towns we should enter.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis seemed like a good idea to me, so I chose twelve scouts,
        one from each of your tribes. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They headed for the hill country and came to the valley of Eshcol
        and explored it. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Rebellion against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>"
      content: "They picked some of its fruit and brought it back to us. And they
        reported, \u2018The land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God has given
        us is indeed a good land.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you rebelled against the command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and refused to go in. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You complained in your tents and said, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        must hate us. That\u2019s why he has brought us here from Egypt\u2014to hand
        us over to the Amorites to be slaughtered. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where can we go? Our brothers have demoralized us with their report.
        They tell us, \u201CThe people of the land are taller and more powerful than
        we are, and their towns are large, with walls rising high into the sky! We
        even saw giants there\u2014the descendants of Anak!\u201D\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I said to you, \u2018Don\u2019t be shocked or afraid of
        them! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is going ahead of you. He
        will fight for you, just as you saw him do in Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you saw how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God cared for
        you all along the way as you traveled through the wilderness, just as a father
        cares for his child. Now he has brought you to this place.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut even after all he did, you refused to trust the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'who goes before you looking for the best places to camp, guiding
        you with a pillar of fire by night and a pillar of cloud by day.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> heard your complaining,
        he became very angry. So he solemnly swore, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Not one of you from this wicked generation will live to see
        the good land I swore to give your ancestors, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "except Caleb son of Jephunneh. He will see this land because he has
        followed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> completely. I will give to him and
        his descendants some of the very land he explored during his scouting mission.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was also angry with me
        because of you. He said to me, \u2018Moses, not even you will enter the Promised
        Land! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, your assistant, Joshua son of Nun, will lead the people
        into the land. Encourage him, for he will lead Israel as they take possession
        of it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give the land to your little ones\u2014your innocent children.
        You were afraid they would be captured, but they will be the ones who occupy
        it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As for you, turn around now and go on back through the wilderness
        toward the Red Sea.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:40 '
        content: Hebrew <b>sea of reeds.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen you confessed, \u2018We have sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!
        We will go into the land and fight for it, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God has commanded us.\u2019 So your men strapped on their weapons, thinking
        it would be easy to attack the hill country.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told me to tell you, \u2018Do
        not attack, for I am not with you. If you go ahead on your own, you will
        be crushed by your enemies.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what I told you, but you would not listen. Instead,
        you again rebelled against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s command
        and arrogantly went into the hill country to fight. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the Amorites who lived there came out against you like a swarm
        of bees. They chased and battered you all the way from Seir to Hormah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you returned and wept before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        but he refused to listen. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Remembering Israel\u2019s Wanderings"
      content: "  \u201CThen we turned around and headed back across the wilderness
        toward the Red Sea,[[COMMENT(0)]] just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had instructed me, and we wandered around in the region of Mount Seir for
        a long time.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>sea of reeds.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen at last the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018You have been wandering around in this hill country long enough;
        turn to the north. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Give these orders to the people: \u201CYou will pass through the
        country belonging to your relatives the Edomites, the descendants of Esau,
        who live in Seir. The Edomites will feel threatened, so be careful. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not bother them, for I have given them all the hill country around
        Mount Seir as their property, and I will not give you even one square foot
        of their land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you need food to eat or water to drink, pay them for it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has blessed you in everything
        you have done. He has watched your every step through this great wilderness.
        During these forty years, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has been
        with you, and you have lacked nothing.\u201D\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo we bypassed the territory of our relatives, the descendants
        of Esau, who live in Seir. We avoided the road through the Arabah Valley
        that comes up from Elath and Ezion-geber.\u201CThen as we turned north along
        the desert route through Moab, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> warned us, \u2018Do not bother the
        Moabites, the descendants of Lot, or start a war with them. I have given
        them Ar as their property, and I will not give you any of their land.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(A race of giants called the Emites had once lived in the area of
        Ar. They were as strong and numerous and tall as the Anakites, another race
        of giants. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Both the Emites and the Anakites are also known as the Rephaites,
        though the Moabites call them Emites. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In earlier times the Horites had lived in Seir, but they were driven
        out and displaced by the descendants of Esau, just as Israel drove out the
        people of Canaan when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Israel their land.)  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses continued, \u201CThen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said
        to us, \u2018Get moving. Cross the Zered Brook.\u2019 So we crossed the brook.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThirty-eight years passed from the time we first left Kadesh-barnea
        until we finally crossed the Zered Brook! By then, all the men old enough
        to fight in battle had died in the wilderness, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had vowed would happen. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> struck them down until they had all
        been eliminated from the community.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen all the men of fighting age had died, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Today you will cross the border of Moab at Ar "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and enter the land of the Ammonites, the descendants of Lot. But
        do not bother them or start a war with them. I have given the land of Ammon
        to them as their property, and I will not give you any of their land.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(That area was once considered the land of the Rephaites, who had
        lived there, though the Ammonites call them Zamzummites. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were also as strong and numerous and tall as the Anakites. But
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> destroyed them so the Ammonites could occupy
        their land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He had done the same for the descendants of Esau who lived in Seir,
        for he destroyed the Horites so they could settle there in their place. The
        descendants of Esau live there to this day. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A similar thing happened when the Caphtorites from Crete[[COMMENT(0)]]
        invaded and destroyed the Avvites, who had lived in villages in the area
        of Gaza.)  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>from Caphtor.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Moses continued, \u201CThen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said,
        \u2018Now get moving! Cross the Arnon Gorge. Look, I will hand over to you
        Sihon the Amorite, king of Heshbon, and I will give you his land. Attack
        him and begin to occupy the land. "
      comments: []
    - title: Victory over Sihon of Heshbon
      content: "Beginning today I will make people throughout the earth terrified
        because of you. When they hear reports about you, they will tremble with
        dread and fear.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses continued, \u201CFrom the wilderness of Kedemoth I sent ambassadors
        to King Sihon of Heshbon with this proposal of peace:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Let us travel through your land. We will stay on the main road
        and won\u2019t turn off into the fields on either side. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sell us food to eat and water to drink, and we will pay for it. All
        we want is permission to pass through your land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The descendants of Esau who live in Seir allowed us to go through
        their country, and so did the Moabites, who live in Ar. Let us pass through
        until we cross the Jordan into the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our
        God is giving us.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut King Sihon of Heshbon refused to allow us to pass through,
        because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God made Sihon stubborn and
        defiant so he could help you defeat him, as he has now done.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Look,
        I have begun to hand King Sihon and his land over to you. Begin now to conquer
        and occupy his land.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen King Sihon declared war on us and mobilized his forces
        at Jahaz. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God handed him over to us,
        and we crushed him, his sons, and all his people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We conquered all his towns and completely destroyed[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>
        everyone\u2014men, women, and children. Not a single person was spared. </smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: '2:34 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering.
    - title: 
      content: 'We took all the livestock as plunder for ourselves, along with anything
        of value from the towns we ransacked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God also helped us conquer
        Aroer on the edge of the Arnon Gorge, and the town in the gorge, and the
        whole area as far as Gilead. No town had walls too strong for us. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Victory over Og of Bashan
      content: "  \u201CNext we turned and headed for the land of Bashan, where King
        Og and his entire army attacked us at Edrei. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told me, \u2018Do not be afraid
        of him, for I have given you victory over Og and his entire army, and I will
        give you all his land. Treat him just as you treated King Sihon of the Amorites,
        who ruled in Heshbon.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God handed King Og and
        all his people over to us, and we killed them all. Not a single person survived. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We conquered all sixty of his towns\u2014the entire Argob region
        in his kingdom of Bashan. Not a single town escaped our conquest. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These towns were all fortified with high walls and barred gates.
        We also took many unwalled villages at the same time. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We completely destroyed[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> the kingdom of Bashan,
        just as we had destroyed King Sihon of Heshbon. We destroyed all the people
        in every town we conquered\u2014men, women, and children alike. </smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering; also in 3:6b.
    - title: 
      content: 'But we kept all the livestock for ourselves and took plunder from
        all the towns.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo we took the land of the two Amorite kings east of the Jordan
        River\u2014all the way from the Arnon Gorge to Mount Hermon. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(Mount Hermon is called Sirion by the Sidonians, and the Amorites
        call it Senir.) '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We had now conquered all the cities on the plateau and all Gilead
        and Bashan, as far as the towns of Salecah and Edrei, which were part of
        Og\u2019s kingdom in Bashan. "
      comments: []
    - title: Land Division East of the Jordan
      content: '(King Og of Bashan was the last survivor of the giant Rephaites.
        His bed was made of iron and was more than thirteen feet long and six feet
        wide.[[COMMENT(0)]] It can still be seen in the Ammonite city of Rabbah.)  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>9 cubits </b>[4.1 meters] <b>long and 4 cubits </b>[1.8
          meters] <b>wide.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen we took possession of this land, I gave to the tribes
        of Reuben and Gad the territory beyond Aroer along the Arnon Gorge, plus
        half of the hill country of Gilead with its towns. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I gave the rest of Gilead and all of Bashan\u2014Og\u2019s former
        kingdom\u2014to the half-tribe of Manasseh. (This entire Argob region of
        Bashan used to be known as the land of the Rephaites. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jair, a leader from the tribe of Manasseh, conquered the whole Argob
        region in Bashan, all the way to the border of the Geshurites and Maacathites.
        Jair renamed this region after himself, calling it the Towns of Jair,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        as it is still known today.) '
      comments:
      - number: '3:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Havvoth-jair.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I gave Gilead to the clan of Makir. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I also gave part of Gilead to the tribes of Reuben and Gad. The
        area I gave them extended from the middle of the Arnon Gorge in the south
        to the Jabbok River on the Ammonite frontier. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They also received the Jordan Valley, all the way from the Sea of
        Galilee down to the Dead Sea,[[COMMENT(0)]] with the Jordan River serving
        as the western boundary. To the east were the slopes of Pisgah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>from Kinnereth to the Sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAt that time I gave this command to the tribes that would live
        east of the Jordan: \u2018Although the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        has given you this land as your property, all your fighting men must cross
        the Jordan ahead of your Israelite relatives, armed and ready to assist them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your wives, children, and numerous livestock, however, may stay behind
        in the towns I have given you. '
      comments: []
    - title: Moses Forbidden to Enter the Land
      content: "When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given security to the rest
        of the Israelites, as he has to you, and when they occupy the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving them across the Jordan River, then you may all return
        here to the land I have given you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAt that time I gave Joshua this charge: \u2018You have seen
        for yourself everything the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has done
        to these two kings. He will do the same to all the kingdoms on the west side
        of the Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not be afraid of the nations there, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will fight for you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAt that time I pleaded with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and said, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018O Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you have only begun
        to show your greatness and the strength of your hand to me, your servant.
        Is there any god in heaven or on earth who can perform such great and mighty
        deeds as you do? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Please let me cross the Jordan to see the wonderful land on the other
        side, the beautiful hill country and the Lebanon mountains.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was angry with me because
        of you, and he would not listen to me. \u2018That\u2019s enough!\u2019 he
        declared. \u2018Speak of it no more. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But go up to Pisgah Peak, and look over the land in every direction.
        Take a good look, but you may not cross the Jordan River. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, commission Joshua and encourage and strengthen him, for
        he will lead the people across the Jordan. He will give them all the land
        you now see before you as their possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Moses Urges Israel to Obey
      content: "  \u201CAnd now, Israel, listen carefully to these decrees and regulations
        that I am about to teach you. Obey them so that you may live, so you may
        enter and occupy the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        your ancestors, is giving you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not add to or subtract from these commands I am giving you. Just
        obey the commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God that I am giving
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou saw for yourself what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did
        to you at Baal-peor. There the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God destroyed
        everyone who had worshiped Baal, the god of Peor. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But all of you who were faithful to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God are still alive today\u2014every one of you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, I now teach you these decrees and regulations just as
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God commanded me, so that you may obey
        them in the land you are about to enter and occupy. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Obey them completely, and you will display your wisdom and intelligence
        among the surrounding nations. When they hear all these decrees, they will
        exclaim, \u2018How wise and prudent are the people of this great nation!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For what great nation has a god as near to them as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God is near to us whenever we call on him? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And what great nation has decrees and regulations as righteous and
        fair as this body of instructions that I am giving you today?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut watch out! Be careful never to forget what you yourself
        have seen. Do not let these memories escape from your mind as long as you
        live! And be sure to pass them on to your children and grandchildren. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Never forget the day when you stood before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God at Mount Sinai,[[COMMENT(0)]] where he told me, \u2018Summon the
        people before me, and I will personally instruct them. Then they will learn
        to fear me as long as they live, and they will teach their children to fear
        me also.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Horeb, </b>another name for Sinai; also in 4:15.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou came near and stood at the foot of the mountain, while
        flames from the mountain shot into the sky. The mountain was shrouded in
        black clouds and deep darkness. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to you from the heart of
        the fire. You heard the sound of his words but didn\u2019t see his form;
        there was only a voice. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He proclaimed his covenant\u2014the Ten Commandments[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014which
        he commanded you to keep, and which he wrote on two stone tablets. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the ten words.</b>
    - title: A Warning against Idolatry
      content: 'It was at that time that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded
        me to teach you his decrees and regulations so you would obey them in the
        land you are about to enter and occupy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut be very careful! You did not see the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        form on the day he spoke to you from the heart of the fire at Mount Sinai. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So do not corrupt yourselves by making an idol in any form\u2014whether
        of a man or a woman, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'an animal on the ground, a bird in the sky, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'a small animal that scurries along the ground, or a fish in the deepest
        sea. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And when you look up into the sky and see the sun, moon, and stars\u2014all
        the forces of heaven\u2014don\u2019t be seduced into worshiping them. The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God gave them to all the peoples of the
        earth. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rescued you from the
        iron-smelting furnace of Egypt in order to make you his very own people and
        his special possession, which is what you are today.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was angry with me because
        of you. He vowed that I would not cross the Jordan River into the good land
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you as your special possession. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will cross the Jordan to occupy the land, but I will not. Instead,
        I will die here on the east side of the river. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So be careful not to break the covenant the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has made with you. Do not make idols of any shape or form, for the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has forbidden this. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is a devouring fire; he
        is a jealous God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn the future, when you have children and grandchildren and
        have lived in the land a long time, do not corrupt yourselves by making idols
        of any kind. This is evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and will arouse his anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CToday I call on heaven and earth as witnesses against you.
        If you break my covenant, you will quickly disappear from the land you are
        crossing the Jordan to occupy. You will live there only a short time; then
        you will be utterly destroyed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will scatter you among the nations,
        where only a few of you will survive. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There, in a foreign land, you will worship idols made from wood and
        stone\u2014gods that neither see nor hear nor eat nor smell. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But from there you will search again for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. And if you search for him with all your heart and soul, you will
        find him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn the distant future, when you are suffering all these things,
        you will finally return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and listen
        to what he tells you. "
      comments: []
    - title: There Is Only One God
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is a merciful God; he
        will not abandon you or destroy you or forget the solemn covenant he made
        with your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow search all of history, from the time God created people
        on the earth until now, and search from one end of the heavens to the other.
        Has anything as great as this ever been seen or heard before? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Has any nation ever heard the voice of God[[COMMENT(0)]] speaking
        from fire\u2014as you did\u2014and survived? "
      comments:
      - number: '4:33 '
        content: Or <b>voice of a god.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Has any other god dared to take a nation for himself out of another
        nation by means of trials, miraculous signs, wonders, war, a strong hand,
        a powerful arm, and terrifying acts? Yet that is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God did for you in Egypt, right before your eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHe showed you these things so you would know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is God and there is no other. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He let you hear his voice from heaven so he could instruct you. He
        let you see his great fire here on earth so he could speak to you from it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because he loved your ancestors, he chose to bless their descendants,
        and he personally brought you out of Egypt with a great display of power. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He drove out nations far greater than you, so he could bring you
        in and give you their land as your special possession, as it is today.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo remember this and keep it firmly in mind: The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is God both in heaven and on earth, and there is no other. "
      comments: []
    - title: Eastern Cities of Refuge
      content: "If you obey all the decrees and commands I am giving you today, all
        will be well with you and your children. I am giving you these instructions
        so you will enjoy a long life in the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you for all time.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Moses set apart three cities of refuge east of the Jordan River. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone who killed another person unintentionally, without previous
        hostility, could flee there to live in safety. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Introduction to Moses\u2019 Second Address"
      content: 'These were the cities: Bezer on the wilderness plateau for the tribe
        of Reuben; Ramoth in Gilead for the tribe of Gad; Golan in Bashan for the
        tribe of Manasseh.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is the body of instruction that Moses presented to the Israelites. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These are the laws, decrees, and regulations that Moses gave to the
        people of Israel when they left Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and as they camped in the valley near Beth-peor east of the Jordan
        River. (This land was formerly occupied by the Amorites under King Sihon,
        who ruled from Heshbon. But Moses and the Israelites destroyed him and his
        people when they came up from Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Israel took possession of his land and that of King Og of Bashan\u2014the
        two Amorite kings east of the Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Israel conquered the entire area from Aroer at the edge of the
        Arnon Gorge all the way to Mount Sirion,[[COMMENT(0)]] also called Mount
        Hermon. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:48 '
        content: As in Syriac version (see also 3:9); Hebrew reads <b>Mount Sion.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: Ten Commandments for the Covenant Community
      content: "  Moses called all the people of Israel together and said, \u201CListen
        carefully, Israel. Hear the decrees and regulations I am giving you today,
        so you may learn them and obey them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God made a covenant with
        us at Mount Sinai.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Horeb, </b>another name for Sinai.
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did not make this covenant with our
        ancestors, but with all of us who are alive today. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At the mountain the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to you face
        to face from the heart of the fire. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I stood as an intermediary between you and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for you were afraid of the fire and did not want to approach the mountain.
        He spoke to me, and I passed his words on to you. This is what he said:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who rescued
        you from the land of Egypt, the place of your slavery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not have any other god but me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not make for yourself an idol of any kind, or an image
        of anything in the heavens or on the earth or in the sea. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must not bow down to them or worship them, for I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, am a jealous God who will not tolerate your affection for any other
        gods. I lay the sins of the parents upon their children; the entire family
        is affected\u2014even children in the third and fourth generations of those
        who reject me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I lavish unfailing love for a thousand generations on those[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who love me and obey my commands.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>for thousands of those.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not misuse the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not let you go unpunished
        if you misuse his name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CObserve the Sabbath day by keeping it holy, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have six days each week for your ordinary work, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but the seventh day is a Sabbath day of rest dedicated to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. On that day no one in your household may do any work. This includes
        you, your sons and daughters, your male and female servants, your oxen and
        donkeys and other livestock, and any foreigners living among you. All your
        male and female servants must rest as you do. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember that you were once slaves in Egypt, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God brought you out with his strong hand and powerful arm. That is why
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has commanded you to rest on the
        Sabbath day.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHonor your father and mother, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God commanded you. Then you will live a long, full life in the land
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not murder.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not commit adultery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not steal.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not testify falsely against your neighbor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not covet your neighbor\u2019s wife. You must not
        covet your neighbor\u2019s house or land, male or female servant, ox or donkey,
        or anything else that belongs to your neighbor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke these words to all of
        you assembled there at the foot of the mountain. He spoke with a loud voice
        from the heart of the fire, surrounded by clouds and deep darkness. This
        was all he said at that time, and he wrote his words on two stone tablets
        and gave them to me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut when you heard the voice from the heart of the darkness,
        while the mountain was blazing with fire, all your tribal leaders and elders
        came to me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They said, \u2018Look, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God has
        shown us his glory and greatness, and we have heard his voice from the heart
        of the fire. Today we have seen that God can speak to us humans, and yet
        we live! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now, why should we risk death again? If the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God speaks to us again, we will certainly die and be consumed by this
        awesome fire. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can any living thing hear the voice of the living God from the heart
        of the fire as we did and yet survive? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Go yourself and listen to what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our
        God says. Then come and tell us everything he tells you, and we will listen
        and obey.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> heard the request you made
        to me. And he said, \u2018I have heard what the people said to you, and they
        are right. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, that they would always have hearts like this, that they might
        fear me and obey all my commands! If they did, they and their descendants
        would prosper forever. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Go and tell them, \u201CReturn to your tents.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you stand here with me so I can give you all my commands, decrees,
        and regulations. You must teach them to the people so they can obey them
        in the land I am giving them as their possession.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Moses told the people, \u201CYou must be careful to obey all the
        commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, following his instructions
        in every detail. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call for Wholehearted Commitment
      content: "  \u201CThese are the commands, decrees, and regulations that the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God commanded me to teach you. You must
        obey them in the land you are about to enter and occupy, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and you and your children and grandchildren must fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God as long as you live. If you obey all his decrees and commands, you
        will enjoy a long life. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen closely, Israel, and be careful to obey. Then all will go
        well with you, and you will have many children in the land flowing with milk
        and honey, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of your ancestors,
        promised you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen, O Israel! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is our God,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> alone.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:4 '
        content: Or <b>The <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span> our
          God is one <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>; </b>or <b>The
          <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span> our God, the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>
          is one; </b>or <b>The <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>
          is our God, the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span> is one.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And you must love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God with all
        your heart, all your soul, and all your strength. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And you must commit yourselves wholeheartedly to these commands that
        I am giving you today. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Repeat them again and again to your children. Talk about them when
        you are at home and when you are on the road, when you are going to bed and
        when you are getting up. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tie them to your hands and wear them on your forehead as reminders. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will soon bring you
        into the land he swore to give you when he made a vow to your ancestors Abraham,
        Isaac, and Jacob. It is a land with large, prosperous cities that you did
        not build. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The houses will be richly stocked with goods you did not produce.
        You will draw water from cisterns you did not dig, and you will eat from
        vineyards and olive trees you did not plant. When you have eaten your fill
        in this land, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'be careful not to forget the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who rescued
        you from slavery in the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and serve
        him. When you take an oath, you must use only his name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not worship any of the gods of neighboring nations, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who lives among you,
        is a jealous God. His anger will flare up against you, and he will wipe you
        from the face of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must not test the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God as you
        did when you complained at Massah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must diligently obey the commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God\u2014all the laws and decrees he has given you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do what is right and good in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        sight, so all will go well with you. Then you will enter and occupy the good
        land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to give your ancestors. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will drive out all the enemies living in the land, just as the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said you would.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn the future your children will ask you, \u2018What is the
        meaning of these laws, decrees, and regulations that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God has commanded us to obey?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen you must tell them, \u2018We were Pharaoh\u2019s slaves
        in Egypt, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> brought us out of Egypt with
        his strong hand. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did miraculous signs and wonders
        before our eyes, dealing terrifying blows against Egypt and Pharaoh and all
        his people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He brought us out of Egypt so he could give us this land he had sworn
        to give our ancestors. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God commanded us to obey
        all these decrees and to fear him so he can continue to bless us and preserve
        our lives, as he has done to this day. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Privilege of Holiness
      content: "  \u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God brings you
        into the land you are about to enter and occupy, he will clear away many
        nations ahead of you: the Hittites, Girgashites, Amorites, Canaanites, Perizzites,
        Hivites, and Jebusites. These seven nations are greater and more numerous
        than you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God hands these nations
        over to you and you conquer them, you must completely destroy[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>
        them. Make no treaties with them and show them no mercy. </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering; also in 7:26.
    - title: 
      content: 'You must not intermarry with them. Do not let your daughters and
        sons marry their sons and daughters, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for they will lead your children away from me to worship other gods.
        Then the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will burn against you,
        and he will quickly destroy you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is what you must do. You must break down their pagan altars
        and shatter their sacred pillars. Cut down their Asherah poles and burn their
        idols. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you are a holy people, who belong to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. Of all the people on earth, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God has chosen you to be his own special treasure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did not set his heart on you
        and choose you because you were more numerous than other nations, for you
        were the smallest of all nations! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rather, it was simply that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> loves
        you, and he was keeping the oath he had sworn to your ancestors. That is
        why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rescued you with such a strong hand from
        your slavery and from the oppressive hand of Pharaoh, king of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Understand, therefore, that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God is indeed God. He is the faithful God who keeps his covenant for a thousand
        generations and lavishes his unfailing love on those who love him and obey
        his commands. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But he does not hesitate to punish and destroy those who reject him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, you must obey all these commands, decrees, and regulations
        I am giving you today.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you listen to these regulations and faithfully obey them,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will keep his covenant of unfailing
        love with you, as he promised with an oath to your ancestors. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will love you and bless you, and he will give you many children.
        He will give fertility to your land and your animals. When you arrive in
        the land he swore to give your ancestors, you will have large harvests of
        grain, new wine, and olive oil, and great herds of cattle, sheep, and goats. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be blessed above all the nations of the earth. None of your
        men or women will be childless, and all your livestock will bear young. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will protect you from all sickness.
        He will not let you suffer from the terrible diseases you knew in Egypt,
        but he will inflict them on all your enemies!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must destroy all the nations the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God hands over to you. Show them no mercy, and do not worship their
        gods, or they will trap you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Perhaps you will think to yourselves, \u2018How can we ever conquer
        these nations that are so much more powerful than we are?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But don\u2019t be afraid of them! Just remember what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God did to Pharaoh and to all the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember the great terrors the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        sent against them. You saw it all with your own eyes! And remember the miraculous
        signs and wonders, and the strong hand and powerful arm with which he brought
        you out of Egypt. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will use this
        same power against all the people you fear. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will send terror[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to drive out the few survivors still hiding from you!  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:20 '
        content: Often rendered <b>the hornet. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo, do not be afraid of those nations, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is among you, and he is a great and awesome God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will drive those nations
        out ahead of you little by little. You will not clear them away all at once,
        otherwise the wild animals would multiply too quickly for you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will hand them over
        to you. He will throw them into complete confusion until they are destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will put their kings in your power, and you will erase their names
        from the face of the earth. No one will be able to stand against you, and
        you will destroy them all.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must burn their idols in fire, and you must not covet the
        silver or gold that covers them. You must not take it or it will become a
        trap to you, for it is detestable to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Remember and Obey
      content: "  \u201CBe careful to obey all the commands I am giving you today.
        Then you will live and multiply, and you will enter and occupy the land the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to give your ancestors. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God led you through
        the wilderness for these forty years, humbling you and testing you to prove
        your character, and to find out whether or not you would obey his commands. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, he humbled you by letting you go hungry and then feeding you
        with manna, a food previously unknown to you and your ancestors. He did it
        to teach you that people do not live by bread alone; rather, we live by every
        word that comes from the mouth of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For all these forty years your clothes didn\u2019t wear out, and
        your feet didn\u2019t blister or swell. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Think about it: Just as a parent disciplines a child, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God disciplines you for your own good.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo obey the commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God by walking in his ways and fearing him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is bringing you into
        a good land of flowing streams and pools of water, with fountains and springs
        that gush out in the valleys and hills. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is a land of wheat and barley; of grapevines, fig trees, and pomegranates;
        of olive oil and honey. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is a land where food is plentiful and nothing is lacking. It is
        a land where iron is as common as stone, and copper is abundant in the hills. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you have eaten your fill, be sure to praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God for the good land he has given you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut that is the time to be careful! Beware that in your plenty
        you do not forget the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and disobey his
        commands, regulations, and decrees that I am giving you today. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For when you have become full and prosperous and have built fine
        homes to live in, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and when your flocks and herds have become very large and your silver
        and gold have multiplied along with everything else, be careful! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not become proud at that time and forget the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, who rescued you from slavery in the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not forget that he led you through the great and terrifying wilderness
        with its poisonous snakes and scorpions, where it was so hot and dry. He
        gave you water from the rock! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He fed you with manna in the wilderness, a food unknown to your ancestors.
        He did this to humble you and test you for your own good. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He did all this so you would never say to yourself, \u2018I have
        achieved this wealth with my own strength and energy.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. He is the one
        who gives you power to be successful, in order to fulfill the covenant he
        confirmed to your ancestors with an oath.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I assure you of this: If you ever forget the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and follow other gods, worshiping and bowing down to them, you will
        certainly be destroyed. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Victory by God\u2019s Grace"
      content: "  \u201CListen, O Israel! Today you are about to cross the Jordan
        River to take over the land belonging to nations much greater and more powerful
        than you. They live in cities with walls that reach to the sky! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people are strong and tall\u2014descendants of the famous Anakite
        giants. You\u2019ve heard the saying, \u2018Who can stand up to the Anakites?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But recognize today that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        is the one who will cross over ahead of you like a devouring fire to destroy
        them. He will subdue them so that you will quickly conquer them and drive
        them out, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has promised.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAfter the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has done this
        for you, don\u2019t say in your hearts, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given us this land because we are such good people!\u2019 No, it is because
        of the wickedness of the other nations that he is pushing them out of your
        way. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is not because you are so good or have such integrity that you
        are about to occupy their land. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        will drive these nations out ahead of you only because of their wickedness,
        and to fulfill the oath he swore to your ancestors Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - title: Remembering the Gold Calf
      content: "You must recognize that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        is not giving you this good land because you are good, for you are not\u2014you
        are a stubborn people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRemember and never forget how angry you made the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God out in the wilderness. From the day you left Egypt until now, you
        have been constantly rebelling against him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even at Mount Sinai[[COMMENT(0)]] you made the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        so angry he was ready to destroy you. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Horeb, </b>another name for Sinai.
    - title: 
      content: 'This happened when I was on the mountain receiving the tablets of
        stone inscribed with the words of the covenant that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had made with you. I was there for forty days and forty nights, and all that
        time I ate no food and drank no water. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me the two tablets on which
        God had written with his own finger all the words he had spoken to you from
        the heart of the fire when you were assembled at the mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAt the end of the forty days and nights, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        handed me the two stone tablets inscribed with the words of the covenant. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Get up! Go
        down immediately, for the people you brought out of Egypt have corrupted
        themselves. How quickly they have turned away from the way I commanded them
        to live! They have melted gold and made an idol for themselves!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> also said to me, \u2018I have
        seen how stubborn and rebellious these people are. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Leave me alone so I may destroy them and erase their name from under
        heaven. Then I will make a mighty nation of your descendants, a nation larger
        and more powerful than they are.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo while the mountain was blazing with fire I turned and came
        down, holding in my hands the two stone tablets inscribed with the terms
        of the covenant. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There below me I could see that you had sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. You had melted gold and made a calf idol for yourselves. How quickly
        you had turned away from the path the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded
        you to follow! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I took the stone tablets and threw them to the ground, smashing
        them before your eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen, as before, I threw myself down before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for forty days and nights. I ate no bread and drank no water because of the
        great sin you had committed by doing what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        hated, provoking him to anger. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I feared that the furious anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        which turned him against you, would drive him to destroy you. But again he
        listened to me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was so angry with Aaron that he wanted
        to destroy him, too. But I prayed for Aaron, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        spared him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I took your sin\u2014the calf you had made\u2014and I melted it down
        in the fire and ground it into fine dust. Then I threw the dust into the
        stream that flows down the mountain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou also made the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> angry at Taberah,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Massah,[[COMMENT(1)]] and Kibroth-hattaavah.[[COMMENT(2)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:22a '
        content: "<b>Taberah </b>means \u201Cplace of burning.\u201D See Num 11:1-3."
      - number: '9:22b '
        content: "<b>Massah </b>means \u201Cplace of testing.\u201D See Exod 17:1-7."
      - number: '9:22c '
        content: "<b>Kibroth-hattaavah </b>means \u201Cgraves of gluttony.\u201D
          See Num 11:31-34."
    - title: 
      content: "And at Kadesh-barnea the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent you out
        with this command: \u2018Go up and take over the land I have given you.\u2019
        But you rebelled against the command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God and refused to put your trust in him or obey him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, you have been rebelling against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as long as I have known you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThat is why I threw myself down before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for forty days and nights\u2014for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said he
        would destroy you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and said, \u2018O Sovereign
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, do not destroy them. They are your own people.
        They are your special possession, whom you redeemed from Egypt by your mighty
        power and your strong hand. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Please overlook the stubbornness and the awful sin of these people,
        and remember instead your servants Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you destroy these people, the Egyptians will say, \u201CThe Israelites
        died because the <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>wasn\u2019t able to bring them
        to the land he had promised to give them.\u201D Or they might say, \u201CHe
        destroyed them because he hated them; he deliberately took them into the
        wilderness to slaughter them.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A New Copy of the Covenant
      content: "  \u201CAt that time the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me,
        \u2018Chisel out two stone tablets like the first ones. Also make a wooden
        Ark\u2014a sacred chest to store them in. Come up to me on the mountain, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and I will write on the tablets the same words that were on the ones
        you smashed. Then place the tablets in the Ark.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo I made an Ark of acacia wood and cut two stone tablets like
        the first two. Then I went up the mountain with the tablets in my hand. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Once again the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> wrote the Ten Commandments[[COMMENT(0)]]
        on the tablets and gave them to me. They were the same words the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had spoken to you from the heart of the fire on the day you were assembled
        at the foot of the mountain. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the ten words.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then I turned and came down the mountain and placed the tablets in
        the Ark of the Covenant, which I had made, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded me. And the tablets are still there in the Ark.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(The people of Israel set out from the wells of the people of Jaakan[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and traveled to Moserah, where Aaron died and was buried. His son Eleazar
        ministered as high priest in his place. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:6 '
        content: Or <b>set out from Beeroth of Bene-jaakan.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they journeyed to Gudgodah, and from there to Jotbathah, a land
        with many brooks and streams. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At that time the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> set apart the tribe
        of Levi to carry the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Covenant,
        and to stand before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> as his ministers, and
        to pronounce blessings in his name. These are their duties to this day. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why the Levites have no share of property or possession of
        land among the other Israelite tribes. The <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>himself
        is their special possession, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        told them.)  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAs for me, I stayed on the mountain in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence for forty days and nights, as I had done the first time. And once
        again the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> listened to my pleas and agreed not
        to destroy you. "
      comments: []
    - title: A Call to Love and Obedience
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018Get up and
        resume the journey, and lead the people to the land I swore to give to their
        ancestors, so they may take possession of it.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd now, Israel, what does the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God require of you? He requires only that you fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, and live in a way that pleases him, and love him and serve him
        with all your heart and soul. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you must always obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s commands
        and decrees that I am giving you today for your own good.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, the highest heavens and the earth and everything in it
        all belong to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> chose your ancestors as the objects
        of his love. And he chose you, their descendants, above all other nations,
        as is evident today. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, change your hearts[[COMMENT(0)]] and stop being stubborn.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>circumcise the foreskin of your hearts.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is the God of
        gods and Lord of lords. He is the great God, the mighty and awesome God,
        who shows no partiality and cannot be bribed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He ensures that orphans and widows receive justice. He shows love
        to the foreigners living among you and gives them food and clothing. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So you, too, must show love to foreigners, for you yourselves were
        once foreigners in the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and worship
        him and cling to him. Your oaths must be in his name alone. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He alone is your God, the only one who is worthy of your praise,
        the one who has done these mighty miracles that you have seen with your own
        eyes. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CYou must love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and
        always obey his requirements, decrees, regulations, and commands. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Keep in mind that I am not talking now to your children, who have
        never experienced the discipline of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God or seen his greatness and his strong hand and powerful arm. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They didn\u2019t see the miraculous signs and wonders he performed
        in Egypt against Pharaoh and all his land. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They didn\u2019t see what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did to
        the armies of Egypt and to their horses and chariots\u2014how he drowned
        them in the Red Sea[[COMMENT(0)]] as they were chasing you. He destroyed
        them, and they have not recovered to this very day!  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>sea of reeds.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYour children didn\u2019t see how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        cared for you in the wilderness until you arrived here. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They didn\u2019t see what he did to Dathan and Abiram (the sons of
        Eliab, a descendant of Reuben) when the earth opened its mouth in the Israelite
        camp and swallowed them, along with their households and tents and every
        living thing that belonged to them. "
      comments: []
    - title: The Blessings of Obedience
      content: 'But you have seen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> perform all these
        mighty deeds with your own eyes!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, be careful to obey every command I am giving you
        today, so you may have strength to go in and take over the land you are about
        to enter. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you obey, you will enjoy a long life in the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        swore to give to your ancestors and to you, their descendants\u2014a land
        flowing with milk and honey! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the land you are about to enter and take over is not like the
        land of Egypt from which you came, where you planted your seed and made irrigation
        ditches with your foot as in a vegetable garden. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rather, the land you will soon take over is a land of hills and valleys
        with plenty of rain\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'a land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God cares for. He
        watches over it through each season of the year!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you carefully obey the commands I am giving you today, and
        if you love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and serve him with all
        your heart and soul, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then he will send the rains in their proper seasons\u2014the early
        and late rains\u2014so you can bring in your harvests of grain, new wine,
        and olive oil. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will give you lush pastureland for your livestock, and you yourselves
        will have all you want to eat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut be careful. Don\u2019t let your heart be deceived so that
        you turn away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and serve and worship
        other gods. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you do, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger will burn
        against you. He will shut up the sky and hold back the rain, and the ground
        will fail to produce its harvests. Then you will quickly die in that good
        land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is giving you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo commit yourselves wholeheartedly to these words of mine.
        Tie them to your hands and wear them on your forehead as reminders. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Teach them to your children. Talk about them when you are at home
        and when you are on the road, when you are going to bed and when you are
        getting up. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Write them on the doorposts of your house and on your gates, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'so that as long as the sky remains above the earth, you and your
        children may flourish in the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to
        give your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBe careful to obey all these commands I am giving you. Show
        love to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God by walking in his ways and
        holding tightly to him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will drive out all the nations
        ahead of you, though they are much greater and stronger than you, and you
        will take over their land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wherever you set foot, that land will be yours. Your frontiers will
        stretch from the wilderness in the south to Lebanon in the north, and from
        the Euphrates River in the east to the Mediterranean Sea in the west.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:24 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to the western sea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'No one will be able to stand against you, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will cause the people to fear and dread you, as he promised, wherever
        you go in the whole land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, today I am giving you the choice between a blessing and
        a curse! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be blessed if you obey the commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God that I am giving you today. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you will be cursed if you reject the commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and turn away from him and worship gods you have not known before.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God brings you into
        the land and helps you take possession of it, you must pronounce the blessing
        at Mount Gerizim and the curse at Mount Ebal. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(These two mountains are west of the Jordan River in the land of
        the Canaanites who live in the Jordan Valley,[[COMMENT(0)]] near the town
        of Gilgal, not far from the oaks of Moreh.) '
      comments:
      - number: '11:30 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Arabah.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For you are about to cross the Jordan River to take over the land
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you. When you take that
        land and are living in it, '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Chosen Place for Worship"
      content: "  \u201CThese are the decrees and regulations you must be careful
        to obey when you live in the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        God of your ancestors, is giving you. You must obey them as long as you live.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you drive out the nations that live there, you must destroy
        all the places where they worship their gods\u2014high on the mountains,
        up on the hills, and under every green tree. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Break down their altars and smash their sacred pillars. Burn their
        Asherah poles and cut down their carved idols. Completely erase the names
        of their gods!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo not worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God in
        the way these pagan peoples worship their gods. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rather, you must seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God at
        the place of worship he himself will choose from among all the tribes\u2014the
        place where his name will be honored. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There you will bring your burnt offerings, your sacrifices, your
        tithes, your sacred offerings, your offerings to fulfill a vow, your voluntary
        offerings, and your offerings of the firstborn animals of your herds and
        flocks. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There you and your families will feast in the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, and you will rejoice in all you have accomplished because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has blessed you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYour pattern of worship will change. Today all of you are doing
        as you please, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'because you have not yet arrived at the place of rest, the land the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you as your special possession. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you will soon cross the Jordan River and live in the land the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you. When he gives you rest
        from all your enemies and you\u2019re living safely in the land, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "you must bring everything I command you\u2014your burnt offerings,
        your sacrifices, your tithes, your sacred offerings, and your offerings to
        fulfill a vow\u2014to the designated place of worship, the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God chooses for his name to be honored.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must celebrate there in the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God with your sons and daughters and all your servants. And remember
        to include the Levites who live in your towns, for they will receive no allotment
        of land among you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be careful not to sacrifice your burnt offerings just anywhere you
        like. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You may do so only at the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        choose within one of your tribal territories. There you must offer your burnt
        offerings and do everything I command you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you may butcher your animals and eat their meat in any
        town whenever you want. You may freely eat the animals with which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God blesses you. All of you, whether ceremonially clean or unclean,
        may eat that meat, just as you now eat gazelle and deer. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you must not consume the blood. You must pour it out on the ground
        like water.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you may not eat your offerings in your hometown\u2014neither
        the tithe of your grain and new wine and olive oil, nor the firstborn of
        your flocks and herds, nor any offering to fulfill a vow, nor your voluntary
        offerings, nor your sacred offerings. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must eat these in the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God at the place he will choose. Eat them there with your children,
        your servants, and the Levites who live in your towns, celebrating in the
        presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God in all you do. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And be very careful never to neglect the Levites as long as you live
        in your land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God expands your
        territory as he has promised, and you have the urge to eat meat, you may
        freely eat meat whenever you want. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It might happen that the designated place of worship\u2014the place
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God chooses for his name to be honored\u2014is
        a long way from your home. If so, you may butcher any of the cattle, sheep,
        or goats the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given you, and you may freely
        eat the meat in your hometown, as I have commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone, whether ceremonially clean or unclean, may eat that meat,
        just as you do now with gazelle and deer. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But never consume the blood, for the blood is the life, and you must
        not consume the lifeblood with the meat. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, pour out the blood on the ground like water. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not consume the blood, so that all may go well with you and your
        children after you, because you will be doing what pleases the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTake your sacred gifts and your offerings given to fulfill
        a vow to the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> chooses. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must offer the meat and blood of your burnt offerings on the
        altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. The blood of your other
        sacrifices must be poured out on the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, but you may eat the meat. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be careful to obey all my commands, so that all will go well with
        you and your children after you, because you will be doing what is good and
        pleasing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God goes ahead of
        you and destroys the nations and you drive them out and live in their land, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "do not fall into the trap of following their customs and worshiping
        their gods. Do not inquire about their gods, saying, \u2018How do these nations
        worship their gods? I want to follow their example.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must not worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God the
        way the other nations worship their gods, for they perform for their gods
        every detestable act that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> hates. They even
        burn their sons and daughters as sacrifices to their gods.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Warning against Idolatry
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CSuppose there are prophets among you or those
        who dream dreams about the future, and they promise you signs or miracles, "
      comments:
      - number: '13:1 '
        content: '  Verses 13:1-18 are numbered 13:2-19 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: "and the predicted signs or miracles occur. If they then say, \u2018Come,
        let us worship other gods\u2019\u2014gods you have not known before\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'do not listen to them. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is
        testing you to see if you truly love him with all your heart and soul. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Serve only the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and fear him
        alone. Obey his commands, listen to his voice, and cling to him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The false prophets or visionaries who try to lead you astray must
        be put to death, for they encourage rebellion against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, who redeemed you from slavery and brought you out of the land of
        Egypt. Since they try to lead you astray from the way the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God commanded you to live, you must put them to death. In this way you
        will purge the evil from among you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSuppose someone secretly entices you\u2014even your brother,
        your son or daughter, your beloved wife, or your closest friend\u2014and
        says, \u2018Let us go worship other gods\u2019\u2014gods that neither you
        nor your ancestors have known. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They might suggest that you worship the gods of peoples who live
        nearby or who come from the ends of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But do not give in or listen. Have no pity, and do not spare or protect
        them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must put them to death! Strike the first blow yourself, and then
        all the people must join in. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Stone the guilty ones to death because they have tried to draw you
        away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who rescued you from
        the land of Egypt, the place of slavery. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then all Israel will hear about it and be afraid, and no one will
        act so wickedly again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you begin living in the towns the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you, you may hear "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "that scoundrels among you are leading their fellow citizens astray
        by saying, \u2018Let us go worship other gods\u2019\u2014gods you have not
        known before. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In such cases, you must examine the facts carefully. If you find
        that the report is true and such a detestable act has been committed among
        you, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: you must attack that town and completely destroy[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>
        all its inhabitants, as well as all the livestock. </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: '13:15 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering; similarly in
          13:17.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you must pile all the plunder in the middle of the open square
        and burn it. Burn the entire town as a burnt offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. That town must remain a ruin forever; it may never be rebuilt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Keep none of the plunder that has been set apart for destruction.
        Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will turn from his fierce anger and
        be merciful to you. He will have compassion on you and make you a large nation,
        just as he swore to your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Ceremonially Clean and Unclean Animals
      content: "  \u201CSince you are the people of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, never cut yourselves or shave the hair above your foreheads in
        mourning for the dead. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have been set apart as holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, and he has chosen you from all the nations of the earth to be his
        own special treasure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not eat any detestable animals that are ceremonially
        unclean. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These are the animals[[COMMENT(0)]] you may eat: the ox, the sheep,
        the goat, '
      comments:
      - number: '14:4 '
        content: The identification of some of the animals and birds listed in this
          chapter is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'the deer, the gazelle, the roe deer, the wild goat, the addax, the
        antelope, and the mountain sheep.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou may eat any animal that has completely split hooves and
        chews the cud, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but if the animal doesn\u2019t have both, it may not be eaten. So
        you may not eat the camel, the hare, or the hyrax.[[COMMENT(0)]] They chew
        the cud but do not have split hooves, so they are ceremonially unclean for
        you. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:7 '
        content: Or <b>coney, </b>or <b>rock badger.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And you may not eat the pig. It has split hooves but does not chew
        the cud, so it is ceremonially unclean for you. You may not eat the meat
        of these animals or even touch their carcasses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COf all the marine animals, you may eat whatever has both fins
        and scales. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You may not, however, eat marine animals that do not have both fins
        and scales. They are ceremonially unclean for you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou may eat any bird that is ceremonially clean. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These are the birds you may not eat: the griffon vulture, the bearded
        vulture, the black vulture, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the kite, the falcon, buzzards of all kinds, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'ravens of all kinds, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the eagle owl, the short-eared owl, the seagull, hawks of all kinds, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the little owl, the great owl, the barn owl, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the desert owl, the Egyptian vulture, the cormorant, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the stork, herons of all kinds, the hoopoe, and the bat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll winged insects that walk along the ground are ceremonially
        unclean for you and may not be eaten. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you may eat any winged bird or insect that is ceremonially clean.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Giving of Tithes
      content: "\u201CYou must not eat anything that has died a natural death. You
        may give it to a foreigner living in your town, or you may sell it to a stranger.
        But do not eat it yourselves, for you are set apart as holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.\u201CYou must not cook a young goat in its mother\u2019s milk.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must set aside a tithe of your crops\u2014one-tenth of
        all the crops you harvest each year. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Bring this tithe to the designated place of worship\u2014the place
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God chooses for his name to be honored\u2014and
        eat it there in his presence. This applies to your tithes of grain, new wine,
        olive oil, and the firstborn males of your flocks and herds. Doing this will
        teach you always to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God blesses you
        with a good harvest, the place of worship he chooses for his name to be honored
        might be too far for you to bring the tithe. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If so, you may sell the tithe portion of your crops and herds, put
        the money in a pouch, and go to the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has chosen. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you arrive, you may use the money to buy any kind of food you
        want\u2014cattle, sheep, goats, wine, or other alcoholic drink. Then feast
        there in the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and celebrate
        with your household. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And do not neglect the Levites in your town, for they will receive
        no allotment of land among you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAt the end of every third year, bring the entire tithe of that
        year\u2019s harvest and store it in the nearest town. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Release for Debtors
      content: "  \u201CAt the end of every seventh year you must cancel the debts
        of everyone who owes you money. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is how it must be done. Everyone must cancel the loans they
        have made to their fellow Israelites. They must not demand payment from their
        neighbors or relatives, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s time of
        release has arrived. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This release from debt, however, applies only to your fellow Israelites\u2014not
        to the foreigners living among you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThere should be no poor among you, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will greatly bless you in the land he is giving you as a special
        possession. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will receive this blessing if you are careful to obey all the
        commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God that I am giving you
        today. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will bless you as he has
        promised. You will lend money to many nations but will never need to borrow.
        You will rule many nations, but they will not rule over you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if there are any poor Israelites in your towns when you
        arrive in the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you,
        do not be hard-hearted or tightfisted toward them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, be generous and lend them whatever they need. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not be mean-spirited and refuse someone a loan because the year
        for canceling debts is close at hand. If you refuse to make the loan and
        the needy person cries out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you will be
        considered guilty of sin. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give generously to the poor, not grudgingly, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will bless you in everything you do. '
      comments: []
    - title: Release for Hebrew Slaves
      content: 'There will always be some in the land who are poor. That is why I
        am commanding you to share freely with the poor and with other Israelites
        in need.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf a fellow Hebrew sells himself or herself to be your servant[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and serves you for six years, in the seventh year you must set that servant
        free.  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:12 '
        content: Or <b>If a Hebrew man or woman is sold to you.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you release a male servant, do not send him away empty-handed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give him a generous farewell gift from your flock, your threshing
        floor, and your winepress. Share with him some of the bounty with which the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has blessed you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember that you were once slaves in the land of Egypt and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God redeemed you! That is why I am giving you this command.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut suppose your servant says, \u2018I will not leave you,\u2019
        because he loves you and your family, and he has done well with you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that case, take an awl and push it through his earlobe into the
        door. After that, he will be your servant for life. And do the same for your
        female servants.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Sacrificing Firstborn Male Animals
      content: "\u201CYou must not consider it a hardship when you release your servants.
        Remember that for six years they have given you services worth double the
        wages of hired workers, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will
        bless you in all you do.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must set aside for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God all the firstborn males from your flocks and herds. Do not use the firstborn
        of your herds to work your fields, and do not shear the firstborn of your
        flocks. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, you and your family must eat these animals in the presence
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God each year at the place he chooses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if this firstborn animal has any defect, such as lameness or
        blindness, or if anything else is wrong with it, you must not sacrifice it
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, use it for food for your family in your hometown. Anyone,
        whether ceremonially clean or unclean, may eat it, just as anyone may eat
        a gazelle or deer. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Passover and the Festival of Unleavened Bread
      content: "  \u201CIn honor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, celebrate
        the Passover each year in the early spring, in the month of Abib,[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Abib,
        the first month of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar, usually occurs within
        the months of March and April.</smallcaps> for that was the month in which
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God brought you out of Egypt by night. "
      comments:
      - number: '16:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Observe the month of Abib, and keep the Passover unto
          the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span> your God. </b>
    - title: 
      content: "Your Passover sacrifice may be from either the flock or the herd,
        and it must be sacrificed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God at
        the designated place of worship\u2014the place he chooses for his name to
        be honored. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Eat it with bread made without yeast. For seven days the bread you
        eat must be made without yeast, as when you escaped from Egypt in such a
        hurry. Eat this bread\u2014the bread of suffering\u2014so that as long as
        you live you will remember the day you departed from Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let no yeast be found in any house throughout your land for those
        seven days. And when you sacrifice the Passover lamb on the evening of the
        first day, do not let any of the meat remain until the next morning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou may not sacrifice the Passover in just any of the towns
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must offer it only at the designated place of worship\u2014the
        place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God chooses for his name to be
        honored. Sacrifice it there in the evening as the sun goes down on the anniversary
        of your exodus from Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Roast the lamb and eat it in the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God chooses. Then you may go back to your tents the next morning. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Festival of Harvest
      content: 'For the next six days you may not eat any bread made with yeast.
        On the seventh day proclaim another holy day in honor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, and no work may be done on that day.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCount off seven weeks from when you first begin to cut the
        grain at the time of harvest. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then celebrate the Festival of Harvest[[COMMENT(0)]] to honor the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. Bring him a voluntary offering in proportion
        to the blessings you have received from him. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Festival of Weeks; </b>also in 16:16. This was later called
          the Festival of Pentecost (see Acts 2:1). It is celebrated today as Shavuot
          (or Shabuoth).
    - title: 
      content: 'This is a time to celebrate before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God at the designated place of worship he will choose for his name to
        be honored. Celebrate with your sons and daughters, your male and female
        servants, the Levites from your towns, and the foreigners, orphans, and widows
        who live among you. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Festival of Shelters
      content: 'Remember that you were once slaves in Egypt, so be careful to obey
        all these decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must observe the Festival of Shelters[[COMMENT(0)]] for
        seven days at the end of the harvest season, after the grain has been threshed
        and the grapes have been pressed. "
      comments:
      - number: '16:13 '
        content: Or <b>Festival of Booths, </b>or <b>Festival of Tabernacles; </b>also
          in 16:16. This was earlier called the Festival of the Final Harvest or
          Festival of Ingathering (see Exod 23:16b). It is celebrated today as Sukkot
          (or Succoth).
    - title: 
      content: 'This festival will be a happy time of celebrating with your sons
        and daughters, your male and female servants, and the Levites, foreigners,
        orphans, and widows from your towns. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For seven days you must celebrate this festival to honor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God at the place he chooses, for it is he who blesses you with bountiful
        harvests and gives you success in all your work. This festival will be a
        time of great joy for all.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEach year every man in Israel must celebrate these three festivals:
        the Festival of Unleavened Bread, the Festival of Harvest, and the Festival
        of Shelters. On each of these occasions, all men must appear before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God at the place he chooses, but they must not appear before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        without a gift for him. "
      comments: []
    - title: Justice for the People
      content: 'All must give as they are able, according to the blessings given
        to them by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAppoint judges and officials for yourselves from each of your
        tribes in all the towns the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving
        you. They must judge the people fairly. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must never twist justice or show partiality. Never accept a bribe,
        for bribes blind the eyes of the wise and corrupt the decisions of the godly. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let true justice prevail, so you may live and occupy the land that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must never set up a wooden Asherah pole beside the altar
        you build for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CNever sacrifice sick or defective cattle, sheep, or goats
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, for he detests such gifts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you begin living in the towns the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you, a man or woman among you might do evil in the sight
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and violate the covenant. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For instance, they might serve other gods or worship the sun, the
        moon, or any of the stars\u2014the forces of heaven\u2014which I have strictly
        forbidden. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you hear about it, investigate the matter thoroughly. If it
        is true that this detestable thing has been done in Israel, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then the man or woman who has committed such an evil act must be
        taken to the gates of the town and stoned to death. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But never put a person to death on the testimony of only one witness.
        There must always be two or three witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The witnesses must throw the first stones, and then all the people
        may join in. In this way, you will purge the evil from among you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSuppose a case arises in a local court that is too hard for
        you to decide\u2014for instance, whether someone is guilty of murder or only
        of manslaughter, or a difficult lawsuit, or a case involving different kinds
        of assault. Take such legal cases to the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will choose, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and present them to the Levitical priests or the judge on duty at
        that time. They will hear the case and declare the verdict. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must carry out the verdict they announce and the sentence they
        prescribe at the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> chooses. You must
        do exactly what they say. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After they have interpreted the law and declared their verdict, the
        sentence they impose must be fully executed; do not modify it in any way. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone arrogant enough to reject the verdict of the judge or of the
        priest who represents the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God must die.
        In this way you will purge the evil from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - title: Guidelines for a King
      content: 'Then everyone else will hear about it and be afraid to act so arrogantly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou are about to enter the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you. When you take it over and settle there, you may think,
        \u2018We should select a king to rule over us like the other nations around
        us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If this happens, be sure to select as king the man the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God chooses. You must appoint a fellow Israelite; he may not be a foreigner.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe king must not build up a large stable of horses for himself
        or send his people to Egypt to buy horses, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has told you, \u2018You must never return to Egypt.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The king must not take many wives for himself, because they will
        turn his heart away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And he must not
        accumulate large amounts of wealth in silver and gold for himself.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen he sits on the throne as king, he must copy for himself
        this body of instruction on a scroll in the presence of the Levitical priests. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He must always keep that copy with him and read it daily as long
        as he lives. That way he will learn to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        his God by obeying all the terms of these instructions and decrees. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Gifts for the Priests and Levites
      content: "  \u201CRemember that the Levitical priests\u2014that is, the whole
        of the tribe of Levi\u2014will receive no allotment of land among the other
        tribes in Israel. Instead, the priests and Levites will eat from the special
        gifts given to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for that is their share. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will have no land of their own among the Israelites. The <smallcaps>Lord
        </smallcaps>himself is their special possession, just as he promised them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThese are the parts the priests may claim as their share from
        the cattle, sheep, and goats that the people bring as offerings: the shoulder,
        the cheeks, and the stomach. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must also give to the priests the first share of the grain, the
        new wine, the olive oil, and the wool at shearing time. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God chose the tribe of Levi
        out of all your tribes to minister in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        name forever.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSuppose a Levite chooses to move from his town in Israel, wherever
        he is living, to the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> chooses for worship. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He may minister there in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        his God, just like all his fellow Levites who are serving the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        there. '
      comments: []
    - title: A Call to Holy Living
      content: 'He may eat his share of the sacrifices and offerings, even if he
        also receives support from his family.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you enter the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God is giving you, be very careful not to imitate the detestable customs
        of the nations living there. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For example, never sacrifice your son or daughter as a burnt offering.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        And do not let your people practice fortune-telling, or use sorcery, or interpret
        omens, or engage in witchcraft, '
      comments:
      - number: '18:10 '
        content: Or <b>never make your son or daughter pass through the fire.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'or cast spells, or function as mediums or psychics, or call forth
        the spirits of the dead. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone who does these things is detestable to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        It is because the other nations have done these detestable things that the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will drive them out ahead of you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you must be blameless before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. '
      comments: []
    - title: True and False Prophets
      content: "The nations you are about to displace consult sorcerers and fortune-tellers,
        but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God forbids you to do such things.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses continued, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will
        raise up for you a prophet like me from among your fellow Israelites. You
        must listen to him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For this is what you yourselves requested of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God when you were assembled at Mount Sinai.[[COMMENT(0)]] You said,
        \u2018Don\u2019t let us hear the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God anymore or see this blazing fire, for we will die.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Horeb, </b>another name for Sinai.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018What
        they have said is right. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will raise up a prophet like you from among their fellow Israelites.
        I will put my words in his mouth, and he will tell the people everything
        I command him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will personally deal with anyone who will not listen to the messages
        the prophet proclaims on my behalf. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But any prophet who falsely claims to speak in my name or who speaks
        in the name of another god must die.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you may wonder, \u2018How will we know whether or not a
        prophecy is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u2019 "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Cities of Refuge
      content: "  \u201CWhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God destroys the
        nations whose land he is giving you, you will take over their land and settle
        in their towns and homes. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you must set apart three cities of refuge in the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Survey the territory,[[COMMENT(0)]] and divide the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you into three districts, with one of these cities in
        each district. Then anyone who has killed someone can flee to one of the
        cities of refuge for safety.  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:3 '
        content: Or <b>Keep the roads in good repair.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf someone kills another person unintentionally, without previous
        hostility, the slayer may flee to any of these cities to live in safety. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For example, suppose someone goes into the forest with a neighbor
        to cut wood. And suppose one of them swings an ax to chop down a tree, and
        the ax head flies off the handle, killing the other person. In such cases,
        the slayer may flee to one of the cities of refuge to live in safety.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf the distance to the nearest city of refuge is too far, an
        enraged avenger might be able to chase down and kill the person who caused
        the death. Then the slayer would die unfairly, since he had never shown hostility
        toward the person who died. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why I am commanding you to set aside three cities of refuge.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd if the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God enlarges your
        territory, as he swore to your ancestors, and gives you all the land he promised
        them, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "you must designate three additional cities of refuge. (He will give
        you this land if you are careful to obey all the commands I have given you\u2014if
        you always love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and walk in his
        ways.) "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That way you will prevent the death of innocent people in the land
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you as your special possession.
        You will not be held responsible for the death of innocent people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut suppose someone is hostile toward a neighbor and deliberately
        ambushes and murders him and then flees to one of the cities of refuge. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that case, the elders of the murderer\u2019s hometown must send
        agents to the city of refuge to bring him back and hand him over to the dead
        person\u2019s avenger to be put to death. "
      comments: []
    - title: Concern for Justice
      content: 'Do not feel sorry for that murderer! Purge from Israel the guilt
        of murdering innocent people; then all will go well with you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you arrive in the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you as your special possession, you must never steal anyone\u2019s
        land by moving the boundary markers your ancestors set up to mark their property.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not convict anyone of a crime on the testimony of
        only one witness. The facts of the case must be established by the testimony
        of two or three witnesses.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf a malicious witness comes forward and accuses someone of
        a crime, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then both the accuser and accused must appear before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by coming to the priests and judges in office at that time. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The judges must investigate the case thoroughly. If the accuser has
        brought false charges against his fellow Israelite, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you must impose on the accuser the sentence he intended for the other
        person. In this way, you will purge such evil from among you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the rest of the people will hear about it and be afraid to do
        such an evil thing. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Regulations concerning War
      content: "  \u201CWhen you go out to fight your enemies and you face horses
        and chariots and an army greater than your own, do not be afraid. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, is with you! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you prepare for battle, the priest must come forward to speak
        to the troops. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will say to them, \u2018Listen to me, all you men of Israel! Do
        not be afraid as you go out to fight your enemies today! Do not lose heart
        or panic or tremble before them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is going with you! He
        will fight for you against your enemies, and he will give you victory!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the officers of the army must address the troops and say,
        \u2018Has anyone here just built a new house but not yet dedicated it? If
        so, you may go home! You might be killed in the battle, and someone else
        would dedicate your house. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Has anyone here just planted a vineyard but not yet eaten any of
        its fruit? If so, you may go home! You might die in battle, and someone else
        would eat the first fruit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Has anyone here just become engaged to a woman but not yet married
        her? Well, you may go home and get married! You might die in the battle,
        and someone else would marry her.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the officers will also say, \u2018Is anyone here afraid
        or worried? If you are, you may go home before you frighten anyone else.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the officers have finished speaking to their troops, they will
        appoint the unit commanders.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAs you approach a town to attack it, you must first offer its
        people terms for peace. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If they accept your terms and open the gates to you, then all the
        people inside will serve you in forced labor. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if they refuse to make peace and prepare to fight, you must attack
        the town. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God hands the town over
        to you, use your swords to kill every man in the town. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you may keep for yourselves all the women, children, livestock,
        and other plunder. You may enjoy the plunder from your enemies that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has given you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut these instructions apply only to distant towns, not to
        the towns of the nations in the land you will enter. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In those towns that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving
        you as a special possession, destroy every living thing. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must completely destroy[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> the Hittites,
        Amorites, Canaanites, Perizzites, Hivites, and Jebusites, just as the </smallcaps><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has commanded you. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:17 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering.
    - title: 
      content: 'This will prevent the people of the land from teaching you to imitate
        their detestable customs in the worship of their gods, which would cause
        you to sin deeply against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you are attacking a town and the war drags on, you must
        not cut down the trees with your axes. You may eat the fruit, but do not
        cut down the trees. Are the trees your enemies, that you should attack them? "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Cleansing for Unsolved Murder
      content: "  \u201CWhen you are in the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you, someone may be found murdered in a field, and you
        don\u2019t know who committed the murder. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In such a case, your elders and judges must measure the distance
        from the site of the crime to the nearby towns. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the nearest town has been determined, that town\u2019s elders
        must select from the herd a heifer that has never been trained or yoked to
        a plow. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They must lead it down to a valley that has not been plowed or planted
        and that has a stream running through it. There in the valley they must break
        the heifer\u2019s neck. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the Levitical priests must step forward, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has chosen them to minister before him and to pronounce blessings
        in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s name. They are to decide all legal
        and criminal cases.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe elders of the town must wash their hands over the heifer
        whose neck was broken. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they must say, \u2018Our hands did not shed this person\u2019s
        blood, nor did we see it happen. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, forgive your people Israel whom you
        have redeemed. Do not charge your people with the guilt of murdering an innocent
        person.\u2019 Then they will be absolved of the guilt of this person\u2019s
        blood. "
      comments: []
    - title: Marriage to a Captive Woman
      content: "By following these instructions, you will do what is right in the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s sight and will cleanse the guilt of murder
        from your community.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSuppose you go out to war against your enemies and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God hands them over to you, and you take some of them as captives. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And suppose you see among the captives a beautiful woman, and you
        are attracted to her and want to marry her. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If this happens, you may take her to your home, where she must shave
        her head, cut her nails, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and change the clothes she was wearing when she was captured. She
        will stay in your home, but let her mourn for her father and mother for a
        full month. Then you may marry her, and you will be her husband and she will
        be your wife. '
      comments: []
    - title: Rights of the Firstborn
      content: 'But if you marry her and she does not please you, you must let her
        go free. You may not sell her or treat her as a slave, for you have humiliated
        her.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSuppose a man has two wives, but he loves one and not the other,
        and both have given him sons. And suppose the firstborn son is the son of
        the wife he does not love. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the man divides his inheritance, he may not give the larger
        inheritance to his younger son, the son of the wife he loves, as if he were
        the firstborn son. '
      comments: []
    - title: Dealing with a Rebellious Son
      content: "He must recognize the rights of his oldest son, the son of the wife
        he does not love, by giving him a double portion. He is the first son of
        his father\u2019s virility, and the rights of the firstborn belong to him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSuppose a man has a stubborn and rebellious son who will not
        obey his father or mother, even though they discipline him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In such a case, the father and mother must take the son to the elders
        as they hold court at the town gate. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The parents must say to the elders, \u2018This son of ours is stubborn
        and rebellious and refuses to obey. He is a glutton and a drunkard.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: Various Regulations
      content: 'Then all the men of his town must stone him to death. In this way,
        you will purge this evil from among you, and all Israel will hear about it
        and be afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf someone has committed a crime worthy of death and is executed
        and hung on a tree,[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:22 '
        content: Or <b>impaled on a pole; </b>similarly in 21:23.
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CIf you see your neighbor\u2019s ox or sheep or goat wandering
        away, don\u2019t ignore your responsibility.[[COMMENT(0)]] Take it back to
        its owner. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:1 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>don\u2019t hide yourself; </b>similarly in 22:3."
    - title: 
      content: "If its owner does not live nearby or you don\u2019t know who the
        owner is, take it to your place and keep it until the owner comes looking
        for it. Then you must return it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do the same if you find your neighbor\u2019s donkey, clothing, or
        anything else your neighbor loses. Don\u2019t ignore your responsibility.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you see that your neighbor\u2019s donkey or ox has collapsed
        on the road, do not look the other way. Go and help your neighbor get it
        back on its feet!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CA woman must not put on men\u2019s clothing, and a man must
        not wear women\u2019s clothing. Anyone who does this is detestable in the
        sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you happen to find a bird\u2019s nest in a tree or on the
        ground, and there are young ones or eggs in it with the mother sitting in
        the nest, do not take the mother with the young. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You may take the young, but let the mother go, so that you may prosper
        and enjoy a long life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you build a new house, you must build a railing around
        the edge of its flat roof. That way you will not be considered guilty of
        murder if someone falls from the roof.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not plant any other crop between the rows of your
        vineyard. If you do, you are forbidden to use either the grapes from the
        vineyard or the other crop.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not plow with an ox and a donkey harnessed together.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not wear clothing made of wool and linen woven together.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Regulations for Sexual Purity
      content: "\u201CYou must put four tassels on the hem of the cloak with which
        you cover yourself\u2014on the front, back, and sides.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSuppose a man marries a woman, but after sleeping with her,
        he turns against her "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and publicly accuses her of shameful conduct, saying, \u2018When
        I married this woman, I discovered she was not a virgin.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the woman\u2019s father and mother must bring the proof of her
        virginity to the elders as they hold court at the town gate. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Her father must say to them, \u2018I gave my daughter to this man
        to be his wife, and now he has turned against her. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He has accused her of shameful conduct, saying, \u201CI discovered
        that your daughter was not a virgin.\u201D But here is the proof of my daughter\u2019s
        virginity.\u2019 Then they must spread her bed sheet before the elders. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The elders must then take the man and punish him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They must also fine him 100 pieces of silver,[[COMMENT(0)]] which
        he must pay to the woman\u2019s father because he publicly accused a virgin
        of Israel of shameful conduct. The woman will then remain the man\u2019s
        wife, and he may never divorce her.  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>100 [shekels] of silver, </b>about 2.5 pounds or 1.1 kilograms
          in weight.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut suppose the man\u2019s accusations are true, and he can
        show that she was not a virgin. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The woman must be taken to the door of her father\u2019s home, and
        there the men of the town must stone her to death, for she has committed
        a disgraceful crime in Israel by being promiscuous while living in her parents\u2019
        home. In this way, you will purge this evil from among you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf a man is discovered committing adultery, both he and the
        woman must die. In this way, you will purge Israel of such evil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSuppose a man meets a young woman, a virgin who is engaged
        to be married, and he has sexual intercourse with her. If this happens within
        a town, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "you must take both of them to the gates of that town and stone them
        to death. The woman is guilty because she did not scream for help. The man
        must die because he violated another man\u2019s wife. In this way, you will
        purge this evil from among you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if the man meets the engaged woman out in the country,
        and he rapes her, then only the man must die. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do nothing to the young woman; she has committed no crime worthy
        of death. She is as innocent as a murder victim. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Since the man raped her out in the country, it must be assumed that
        she screamed, but there was no one to rescue her.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSuppose a man has intercourse with a young woman who is a virgin
        but is not engaged to be married. If they are discovered, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'he must pay her father fifty pieces of silver.[[COMMENT(0)]] Then
        he must marry the young woman because he violated her, and he may never divorce
        her as long as he lives.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:29 '
        content: 'Hebrew <b>50 [shekels] of silver, </b>about 1.25 pounds or 570
          grams in weight.  '
  - verses:
    - title: Regulations concerning Worship
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CIf a man\u2019s testicles are crushed or
        his penis is cut off, he may not be admitted to the assembly of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:1 '
        content: '  Verses 23:1-25 are numbered 23:2-26 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf a person is illegitimate by birth, neither he nor his descendants
        for ten generations may be admitted to the assembly of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo Ammonite or Moabite or any of their descendants for ten
        generations may be admitted to the assembly of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These nations did not welcome you with food and water when you came
        out of Egypt. Instead, they hired Balaam son of Beor from Pethor in distant
        Aram-naharaim to curse you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God refused to listen to
        Balaam. He turned the intended curse into a blessing because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God loves you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As long as you live, you must never promote the welfare and prosperity
        of the Ammonites or Moabites.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo not detest the Edomites or the Egyptians, because the Edomites
        are your relatives and you lived as foreigners among the Egyptians. "
      comments: []
    - title: Miscellaneous Regulations
      content: 'The third generation of Edomites and Egyptians may enter the assembly
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you go to war against your enemies, be sure to stay away
        from anything that is impure.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAny man who becomes ceremonially defiled because of a nocturnal
        emission must leave the camp and stay away all day. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Toward evening he must bathe himself, and at sunset he may return
        to the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must have a designated area outside the camp where you
        can go to relieve yourself. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Each of you must have a spade as part of your equipment. Whenever
        you relieve yourself, dig a hole with the spade and cover the excrement. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The camp must be holy, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        moves around in your camp to protect you and to defeat your enemies. He must
        not see any shameful thing among you, or he will turn away from you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf slaves should escape from their masters and take refuge
        with you, you must not hand them over to their masters. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them live among you in any town they choose, and do not oppress
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo Israelite, whether man or woman, may become a temple prostitute. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you are bringing an offering to fulfill a vow, you must not
        bring to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God any offering
        from the earnings of a prostitute, whether a man[[COMMENT(0)]] or a woman,
        for both are detestable to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a dog.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo not charge interest on the loans you make to a fellow Israelite,
        whether you loan money, or food, or anything else. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You may charge interest to foreigners, but you may not charge interest
        to Israelites, so that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God may bless
        you in everything you do in the land you are about to enter and occupy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you make a vow to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, be prompt in fulfilling whatever you promised him. For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God demands that you promptly fulfill all your vows, or you will be
        guilty of sin. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'However, it is not a sin to refrain from making a vow. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But once you have voluntarily made a vow, be careful to fulfill your
        promise to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you enter your neighbor\u2019s vineyard, you may eat your
        fill of grapes, but you must not carry any away in a basket. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CSuppose a man marries a woman but she does not please him.
        Having discovered something wrong with her, he writes a document of divorce,
        hands it to her, and sends her away from his house. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When she leaves his house, she is free to marry another man. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if the second husband also turns against her, writes a document
        of divorce, hands it to her, and sends her away, or if he dies, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the first husband may not marry her again, for she has been defiled.
        That would be detestable to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. You must not
        bring guilt upon the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving
        you as a special possession.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CA newly married man must not be drafted into the army or be
        given any other official responsibilities. He must be free to spend one year
        at home, bringing happiness to the wife he has married.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIt is wrong to take a set of millstones, or even just the upper
        millstone, as security for a loan, for the owner uses it to make a living.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf anyone kidnaps a fellow Israelite and treats him as a slave
        or sells him, the kidnapper must die. In this way, you will purge the evil
        from among you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn all cases involving serious skin diseases,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        be careful to follow the instructions of the Levitical priests; obey all
        the commands I have given them. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:8 '
        content: Traditionally rendered <b>leprosy. </b>The Hebrew word used here
          can describe various skin diseases.
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God did to Miriam
        as you were coming from Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you lend anything to your neighbor, do not enter his house
        to pick up the item he is giving as security. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must wait outside while he goes in and brings it out to you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If your neighbor is poor and gives you his cloak as security for
        a loan, do not keep the cloak overnight. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Return the cloak to its owner by sunset so he can stay warm through
        the night and bless you, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will
        count you as righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNever take advantage of poor and destitute laborers, whether
        they are fellow Israelites or foreigners living in your towns. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must pay them their wages each day before sunset because they
        are poor and are counting on it. If you don\u2019t, they might cry out to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> against you, and it would be counted against
        you as sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CParents must not be put to death for the sins of their children,
        nor children for the sins of their parents. Those deserving to die must be
        put to death for their own crimes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTrue justice must be given to foreigners living among you and
        to orphans, and you must never accept a widow\u2019s garment as security
        for her debt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Always remember that you were slaves in Egypt and that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God redeemed you from your slavery. That is why I have given you this
        command.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you are harvesting your crops and forget to bring in a
        bundle of grain from your field, don\u2019t go back to get it. Leave it for
        the foreigners, orphans, and widows. Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will bless you in all you do. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you beat the olives from your olive trees, don\u2019t go over
        the boughs twice. Leave the remaining olives for the foreigners, orphans,
        and widows. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you gather the grapes in your vineyard, don\u2019t glean the
        vines after they are picked. Leave the remaining grapes for the foreigners,
        orphans, and widows. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CSuppose two people take a dispute to court, and the judges
        declare that one is right and the other is wrong. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If the person in the wrong is sentenced to be flogged, the judge
        must command him to lie down and be beaten in his presence with the number
        of lashes appropriate to the crime. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But never give more than forty lashes; more than forty lashes would
        publicly humiliate your neighbor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must not muzzle an ox to keep it from eating as it treads
        out the grain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf two brothers are living together on the same property and
        one of them dies without a son, his widow may not be married to anyone from
        outside the family. Instead, her husband\u2019s brother should marry her
        and have intercourse with her to fulfill the duties of a brother-in-law. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The first son she bears to him will be considered the son of the
        dead brother, so that his name will not be forgotten in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if the man refuses to marry his brother\u2019s widow, she
        must go to the town gate and say to the elders assembled there, \u2018My
        husband\u2019s brother refuses to preserve his brother\u2019s name in Israel\u2014he
        refuses to fulfill the duties of a brother-in-law by marrying me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The elders of the town will then summon him and talk with him. If
        he still refuses and says, \u2018I don\u2019t want to marry her,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the widow must walk over to him in the presence of the elders, pull
        his sandal from his foot, and spit in his face. Then she must declare, \u2018This
        is what happens to a man who refuses to provide his brother with children.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ever afterward in Israel his family will be referred to as \u2018the
        family of the man whose sandal was pulled off\u2019!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf two Israelite men get into a fight and the wife of one tries
        to rescue her husband by grabbing the testicles of the other man, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you must cut off her hand. Show her no pity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must use accurate scales when you weigh out merchandise, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and you must use full and honest measures. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, always use honest weights and measures, so that you may enjoy
        a long life in the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving
        you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All who cheat with dishonest weights and measures are detestable
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNever forget what the Amalekites did to you as you came from
        Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They attacked you when you were exhausted and weary, and they struck
        down those who were straggling behind. They had no fear of God. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Harvest Offerings and Tithes
      content: "  \u201CWhen you enter the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God is giving you as a special possession and you have conquered it and settled
        there, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "put some of the first produce from each crop you harvest into a basket
        and bring it to the designated place of worship\u2014the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God chooses for his name to be honored. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Go to the priest in charge at that time and say to him, \u2018With
        this gift I acknowledge to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God that
        I have entered the land he swore to our ancestors he would give us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The priest will then take the basket from your hand and set it before
        the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must then say in the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, \u2018My ancestor Jacob was a wandering Aramean who went to live
        as a foreigner in Egypt. His family arrived few in number, but in Egypt they
        became a large and mighty nation. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the Egyptians oppressed and humiliated us by making us their
        slaves, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'we cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of our ancestors.
        He heard our cries and saw our hardship, toil, and oppression. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> brought us out of Egypt with a
        strong hand and powerful arm, with overwhelming terror, and with miraculous
        signs and wonders. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He brought us to this place and gave us this land flowing with milk
        and honey! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I have brought you the first
        portion of the harvest you have given me from the ground.\u2019 Then place
        the produce before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and bow to the
        ground in worship before him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Afterward you may go and celebrate because of all the good things
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has given to you and your household.
        Remember to include the Levites and the foreigners living among you in the
        celebration.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEvery third year you must offer a special tithe of your crops.
        In this year of the special tithe you must give your tithes to the Levites,
        foreigners, orphans, and widows, so that they will have enough to eat in
        your towns. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you must declare in the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, \u2018I have taken the sacred gift from my house and have given
        it to the Levites, foreigners, orphans, and widows, just as you commanded
        me. I have not violated or forgotten any of your commands. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have not eaten any of it while in mourning; I have not handled
        it while I was ceremonially unclean; and I have not offered any of it to
        the dead. I have obeyed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God and have done
        everything you commanded me. '
      comments: []
    - title: "A Call to Obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Commands"
      content: "Now look down from your holy dwelling place in heaven and bless your
        people Israel and the land you swore to our ancestors to give us\u2014a land
        flowing with milk and honey.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CToday the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has commanded
        you to obey all these decrees and regulations. So be careful to obey them
        wholeheartedly. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have declared today that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is your
        God. And you have promised to walk in his ways, and to obey his decrees,
        commands, and regulations, and to do everything he tells you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has declared today that you are his
        people, his own special treasure, just as he promised, and that you must
        obey all his commands. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Altar on Mount Ebal
      content: "  Then Moses and the leaders of Israel gave this charge to the people:
        \u201CObey all these commands that I am giving you today. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you cross the Jordan River and enter the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you, set up some large stones and coat them with plaster. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Write this whole body of instruction on them when you cross the river
        to enter the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is giving you\u2014a
        land flowing with milk and honey, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of your ancestors, promised you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you cross the Jordan, set up these stones at Mount Ebal and
        coat them with plaster, as I am commanding you today.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen build an altar there to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, using natural, uncut stones. You must not shape the stones with
        an iron tool. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Build the altar of uncut stones, and use it to offer burnt offerings
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Also sacrifice peace offerings on it, and celebrate by feasting there
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must clearly write all these instructions on the stones coated
        with plaster.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Moses and the Levitical priests addressed all Israel as follows:
        \u201CO Israel, be quiet and listen! Today you have become the people of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. "
      comments: []
    - title: Curses from Mount Ebal
      content: "So you must obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God by keeping
        all these commands and decrees that I am giving you today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That same day Moses also gave this charge to the people: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you cross the Jordan River, the tribes of Simeon, Levi,
        Judah, Issachar, Joseph, and Benjamin must stand on Mount Gerizim to proclaim
        a blessing over the people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the tribes of Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali
        must stand on Mount Ebal to proclaim a curse.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the Levites will shout to all the people of Israel:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who carves or casts an idol and secretly sets
        it up. These idols, the work of craftsmen, are detestable to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019And
        all the people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who dishonors father or mother.\u2019And all
        the people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who steals property from a neighbor by moving
        a boundary marker.\u2019And all the people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who leads a blind person astray on the road.\u2019And
        all the people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who denies justice to foreigners, orphans,
        or widows.\u2019And all the people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who has sexual intercourse with one of his
        father\u2019s wives, for he has violated his father.\u2019And all the people
        will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who has sexual intercourse with an animal.\u2019And
        all the people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who has sexual intercourse with his sister,
        whether she is the daughter of his father or his mother.\u2019And all the
        people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who has sexual intercourse with his mother-in-law.\u2019And
        all the people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who attacks a neighbor in secret.\u2019And
        all the people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Cursed is anyone who accepts payment to kill an innocent person.\u2019And
        all the people will reply, \u2018Amen.\u2019  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Blessings for Obedience
      content: "  \u201CIf you fully obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        and carefully keep all his commands that I am giving you today, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will set you high above all the nations of the world. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will experience all these blessings if you obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your towns and your fieldswill be blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your children and your cropswill be blessed.The offspring of your
        herds and flockswill be blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your fruit baskets and breadboardswill be blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wherever you go and whatever you do,you will be blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will conquer your enemies when
        they attack you. They will attack you from one direction, but they will scatter
        from you in seven!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will guarantee a blessing on
        everything you do and will fill your storehouses with grain. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will bless you in the land he is giving you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you obey the commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and walk in his ways, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will establish
        you as his holy people as he swore he would do. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then all the nations of the world will see that you are a people
        claimed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and they will stand in awe of
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give you prosperity in
        the land he swore to your ancestors to give you, blessing you with many children,
        numerous livestock, and abundant crops. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will send rain at the proper time
        from his rich treasury in the heavens and will bless all the work you do.
        You will lend to many nations, but you will never need to borrow from them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you listen to these commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God that I am giving you today, and if you carefully obey them, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make you the head and not the tail, and
        you will always be on top and never at the bottom. '
      comments: []
    - title: Curses for Disobedience
      content: 'You must not turn away from any of the commands I am giving you today,
        nor follow after other gods and worship them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if you refuse to listen to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and do not obey all the commands and decrees I am giving you today,
        all these curses will come and overwhelm you:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your towns and your fieldswill be cursed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your fruit baskets and breadboardswill be cursed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your children and your cropswill be cursed.The offspring of your
        herds and flockswill be cursed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wherever you go and whatever you do,you will be cursed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>himself will send on you curses,
        confusion, and frustration in everything you do, until at last you are completely
        destroyed for doing evil and abandoning me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will afflict you with diseases until
        none of you are left in the land you are about to enter and occupy. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike you with wasting diseases,
        fever, and inflammation, with scorching heat and drought, and with blight
        and mildew. These disasters will pursue you until you die. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The skies above will be as unyielding as bronze, and the earth beneath
        will be as hard as iron. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will change the rain that falls on
        your land into powder, and dust will pour down from the sky until you are
        destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will cause you to be defeated
        by your enemies. You will attack your enemies from one direction, but you
        will scatter from them in seven! You will be an object of horror to all the
        kingdoms of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your corpses will be food for all the scavenging birds and wild animals,
        and no one will be there to chase them away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will afflict you with the boils
        of Egypt and with tumors, scurvy, and the itch, from which you cannot be
        cured. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike you with madness, blindness,
        and panic. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will grope around in broad daylight like a blind person groping
        in the darkness, but you will not find your way. You will be oppressed and
        robbed continually, and no one will come to save you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou will be engaged to a woman, but another man will sleep
        with her. You will build a house, but someone else will live in it. You will
        plant a vineyard, but you will never enjoy its fruit. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your ox will be butchered before your eyes, but you will not eat
        a single bite of the meat. Your donkey will be taken from you, never to be
        returned. Your sheep and goats will be given to your enemies, and no one
        will be there to help you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will watch as your sons and daughters are taken away as slaves.
        Your heart will break for them, but you won\u2019t be able to help them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A foreign nation you have never heard about will eat the crops you
        worked so hard to grow. You will suffer under constant oppression and harsh
        treatment. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will go mad because of all the tragedy you see around you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will cover your knees and legs with
        incurable boils. In fact, you will be covered from head to foot.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will exile you and your king
        to a nation unknown to you and your ancestors. There in exile you will worship
        gods of wood and stone! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will become an object of horror, ridicule, and mockery among
        all the nations to which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sends you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou will plant much but harvest little, for locusts will eat
        your crops. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will plant vineyards and care for them, but you will not drink
        the wine or eat the grapes, for worms will destroy the vines. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will grow olive trees throughout your land, but you will never
        use the olive oil, for the fruit will drop before it ripens. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will have sons and daughters, but you will lose them, for they
        will be led away into captivity. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Swarms of insects will destroy your trees and crops.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe foreigners living among you will become stronger and stronger,
        while you become weaker and weaker. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will lend money to you, but you will not lend to them. They
        will be the head, and you will be the tail!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you refuse to listen to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and to obey the commands and decrees he has given you, all these
        curses will pursue and overtake you until you are destroyed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These horrors will serve as a sign and warning among you and your
        descendants forever. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you do not serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God with
        joy and enthusiasm for the abundant benefits you have received, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you will serve your enemies whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will send against you. You will be left hungry, thirsty, naked, and lacking
        in everything. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will put an iron yoke on your
        neck, oppressing you harshly until he has destroyed you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring a distant nation
        against you from the end of the earth, and it will swoop down on you like
        a vulture. It is a nation whose language you do not understand, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'a fierce and heartless nation that shows no respect for the old and
        no pity for the young. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its armies will devour your livestock and crops, and you will be
        destroyed. They will leave you no grain, new wine, olive oil, calves, or
        lambs, and you will starve to death. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will attack your cities until all the fortified walls in your
        land\u2014the walls you trusted to protect you\u2014are knocked down. They
        will attack all the towns in the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God has given you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe siege and terrible distress of the enemy\u2019s attack
        will be so severe that you will eat the flesh of your own sons and daughters,
        whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has given you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The most tenderhearted man among you will have no compassion for
        his own brother, his beloved wife, and his surviving children. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will refuse to share with them the flesh he is devouring\u2014the
        flesh of one of his own children\u2014because he has nothing else to eat
        during the siege and terrible distress that your enemy will inflict on all
        your towns. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The most tender and delicate woman among you\u2014so delicate she
        would not so much as touch the ground with her foot\u2014will be selfish
        toward the husband she loves and toward her own son or daughter. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She will hide from them the afterbirth and the new baby she has borne,
        so that she herself can secretly eat them. She will have nothing else to
        eat during the siege and terrible distress that your enemy will inflict on
        all your towns.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you refuse to obey all the words of instruction that are
        written in this book, and if you do not fear the glorious and awesome name
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will overwhelm you and your
        children with indescribable plagues. These plagues will be intense and without
        relief, making you miserable and unbearably sick. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will afflict you with all the diseases of Egypt that you feared
        so much, and you will have no relief. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will afflict you with every sickness
        and plague there is, even those not mentioned in this Book of Instruction,
        until you are destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though you become as numerous as the stars in the sky, few of you
        will be left because you would not listen to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CJust as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has found great pleasure
        in causing you to prosper and multiply, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        find pleasure in destroying you. You will be torn from the land you are about
        to enter and occupy. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will scatter you among all the
        nations from one end of the earth to the other. There you will worship foreign
        gods that neither you nor your ancestors have known, gods made of wood and
        stone! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There among those nations you will find no peace or place to rest.
        And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will cause your heart to tremble, your
        eyesight to fail, and your soul to despair. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your life will constantly hang in the balance. You will live night
        and day in fear, unsure if you will survive. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the morning you will say, \u2018If only it were night!\u2019 And
        in the evening you will say, \u2018If only it were morning!\u2019 For you
        will be terrified by the awful horrors you see around you. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Moses Reviews the Covenant
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]These are the terms of the covenant the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded Moses to make with the Israelites while they were in the land of
        Moab, in addition to the covenant he had made with them at Mount Sinai.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:1a '
        content: '  Verse 29:1 is numbered 28:69 in Hebrew text.  '
      - number: '29:1b '
        content: 'Hebrew <b>Horeb, </b>another name for Sinai.  '
    - title: 
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]]Moses summoned all the Israelites and said to them,
        \u201CYou have seen with your own eyes everything the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        did in the land of Egypt to Pharaoh and to all his servants and to his whole
        country\u2014 "
      comments:
      - number: '29:2 '
        content: '  Verses 29:2-29 are numbered 29:1-28 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'all the great tests of strength, the miraculous signs, and the amazing
        wonders. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But to this day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has not given you
        minds that understand, nor eyes that see, nor ears that hear! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For forty years I led you through the wilderness, yet your clothes
        and sandals did not wear out. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You ate no bread and drank no wine or other alcoholic drink, but
        he provided for you so you would know that he is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen we came here, King Sihon of Heshbon and King Og of Bashan
        came out to fight against us, but we defeated them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We took their land and gave it to the tribes of Reuben and Gad and
        to the half-tribe of Manasseh as their grant of land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, obey the terms of this covenant so that you will
        prosper in everything you do. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All of you\u2014tribal leaders, elders, officers, all the men of
        Israel\u2014are standing today in the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your little ones and your wives are with you, as well as the foreigners
        living among you who chop your wood and carry your water. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You are standing here today to enter into the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is making this covenant, including
        the curses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By entering into the covenant today, he will establish you as his
        people and confirm that he is your God, just as he promised you and as he
        swore to your ancestors Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you are not the only ones with whom I am making this covenant
        with its curses. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am making this covenant both with you who stand here today in the
        presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, and also with the future
        generations who are not standing here today.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou remember how we lived in the land of Egypt and how we traveled
        through the lands of enemy nations as we left. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have seen their detestable practices and their idols[[COMMENT(0)]]
        made of wood, stone, silver, and gold. '
      comments:
      - number: '29:17 '
        content: The Hebrew term (literally <b>round things</b>) probably alludes
          to dung.
    - title: 
      content: "I am making this covenant with you so that no one among you\u2014no
        man, woman, clan, or tribe\u2014will turn away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God to worship these gods of other nations, and so that no root among
        you bears bitter and poisonous fruit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThose who hear the warnings of this curse should not congratulate
        themselves, thinking, \u2018I am safe, even though I am following the desires
        of my own stubborn heart.\u2019 This would lead to utter ruin! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will never pardon such people. Instead
        his anger and jealousy will burn against them. All the curses written in
        this book will come down on them, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        erase their names from under heaven. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will separate them from all the tribes
        of Israel, to pour out on them all the curses of the covenant recorded in
        this Book of Instruction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the generations to come, both your own descendants and
        the foreigners who come from distant lands, will see the devastation of the
        land and the diseases the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> inflicts on it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will exclaim, \u2018The whole land is devastated by sulfur and
        salt. It is a wasteland with nothing planted and nothing growing, not even
        a blade of grass. It is like the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah, Admah and
        Zeboiim, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> destroyed in his intense anger.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd all the surrounding nations will ask, \u2018Why has the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> done this to this land? Why was he so angry?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd the answer will be, \u2018This happened because the people
        of the land abandoned the covenant that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of their ancestors, made with them when he brought them out of the
        land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, they turned away to serve and worship gods they had not
        known before, gods that were not from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger has burned
        against this land, bringing down on it every curse recorded in this book. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In great anger and fury the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> uprooted
        his people from their land and banished them to another land, where they
        still live today!\u2019  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
      content: "  \u201CIn the future, when you experience all these blessings and
        curses I have listed for you, and when you are living among the nations to
        which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has exiled you, take to heart
        all these instructions. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If at that time you and your children return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, and if you obey with all your heart and all your soul all the commands
        I have given you today, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will restore your fortunes.
        He will have mercy on you and gather you back from all the nations where
        he has scattered you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even though you are banished to the ends of the earth,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will gather you from there and bring
        you back again. '
      comments:
      - number: '30:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of the heavens.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will return you to the land
        that belonged to your ancestors, and you will possess that land again. Then
        he will make you even more prosperous and numerous than your ancestors!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will change your heart[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and the hearts of all your descendants, so that you will love him with all
        your heart and soul and so you may live! "
      comments:
      - number: '30:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>circumcise your heart.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will inflict all these curses
        on your enemies and on those who hate and persecute you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you will again obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and keep
        all his commands that I am giving you today.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will then make you
        successful in everything you do. He will give you many children and numerous
        livestock, and he will cause your fields to produce abundant harvests, for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will again delight in being good to you as
        he was to your ancestors. "
      comments: []
    - title: The Choice of Life or Death
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will delight in you if you
        obey his voice and keep the commands and decrees written in this Book of
        Instruction, and if you turn to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        with all your heart and soul.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis command I am giving you today is not too difficult for
        you, and it is not beyond your reach. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is not kept in heaven, so distant that you must ask, \u2018Who
        will go up to heaven and bring it down so we can hear it and obey?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is not kept beyond the sea, so far away that you must ask, \u2018Who
        will cross the sea to bring it to us so we can hear it and obey?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, the message is very close at hand; it is on your lips and in
        your heart so that you can obey it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow listen! Today I am giving you a choice between life and
        death, between prosperity and disaster. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I command you this day to love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God and to keep his commands, decrees, and regulations by walking in
        his ways. If you do this, you will live and multiply, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will bless you and the land you are about to enter and occupy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if your heart turns away and you refuse to listen, and
        if you are drawn away to serve and worship other gods, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then I warn you now that you will certainly be destroyed. You will
        not live a long, good life in the land you are crossing the Jordan to occupy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CToday I have given you the choice between life and death, between
        blessings and curses. Now I call on heaven and earth to witness the choice
        you make. Oh, that you would choose life, so that you and your descendants
        might live! "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Joshua Becomes Israel\u2019s Leader"
      content: '  When Moses had finished giving these instructions[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to all the people of Israel, '
      comments:
      - number: '31:1 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek version; Masoretic Text reads <b>Moses
          went and spoke.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "he said, \u201CI am now 120 years old, and I am no longer able to
        lead you. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has told me, \u2018You will not
        cross the Jordan River.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God himself will cross over
        ahead of you. He will destroy the nations living there, and you will take
        possession of their land. Joshua will lead you across the river, just as
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> promised.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will destroy the nations living
        in the land, just as he destroyed Sihon and Og, the kings of the Amorites. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will hand over to you the people
        who live there, and you must deal with them as I have commanded you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So be strong and courageous! Do not be afraid and do not panic before
        them. For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will personally go ahead
        of you. He will neither fail you nor abandon you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Moses called for Joshua, and as all Israel watched, he said
        to him, \u201CBe strong and courageous! For you will lead these people into
        the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore to their ancestors he
        would give them. You are the one who will divide it among them as their grants
        of land. "
      comments: []
    - title: Public Reading of the Book of Instruction
      content: "Do not be afraid or discouraged, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will personally go ahead of you. He will be with you; he will neither fail
        you nor abandon you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Moses wrote this entire body of instruction in a book and gave
        it to the priests, who carried the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Covenant, and to the elders of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Moses gave them this command: \u201CAt the end of every seventh
        year, the Year of Release, during the Festival of Shelters, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you must read this Book of Instruction to all the people of Israel
        when they assemble before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God at the
        place he chooses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Call them all together\u2014men, women, children, and the foreigners
        living in your towns\u2014so they may hear this Book of Instruction and learn
        to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and carefully obey all the
        terms of these instructions. "
      comments: []
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Disobedience Predicted"
      content: "Do this so that your children who have not known these instructions
        will hear them and will learn to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God. Do this as long as you live in the land you are crossing the Jordan
        to occupy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CThe time
        has come for you to die. Call Joshua and present yourselves at the Tabernacle,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        so that I may commission him there.\u201D So Moses and Joshua went and presented
        themselves at the Tabernacle. "
      comments:
      - number: '31:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 31:14b.
    - title: 
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to them in a pillar
        of cloud that stood at the entrance to the sacred tent.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CYou are about
        to die and join your ancestors. After you are gone, these people will begin
        to worship foreign gods, the gods of the land where they are going. They
        will abandon me and break my covenant that I have made with them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then my anger will blaze forth against them. I will abandon them,
        hiding my face from them, and they will be devoured. Terrible trouble will
        come down on them, and on that day they will say, \u2018These disasters have
        come down on us because God is no longer among us!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At that time I will hide my face from them on account of all the
        evil they commit by worshiping other gods.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo write down the words of this song, and teach it to the people
        of Israel. Help them learn it, so it may serve as a witness for me against
        them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I will bring them into the land I swore to give their ancestors\u2014a
        land flowing with milk and honey. There they will become prosperous, eat
        all the food they want, and become fat. But they will begin to worship other
        gods; they will despise me and break my covenant. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And when great disasters come down on them, this song will stand
        as evidence against them, for it will never be forgotten by their descendants.
        I know the intentions of these people, even now before they have entered
        the land I swore to give them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So that very day Moses wrote down the words of the song and taught
        it to the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commissioned Joshua son of Nun
        with these words: \u201CBe strong and courageous, for you must bring the
        people of Israel into the land I swore to give them. I will be with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Moses had finished writing this entire body of instruction in
        a book, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "he gave this command to the Levites who carried the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Covenant: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTake this Book of Instruction and place it beside the Ark of
        the Covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, so it may remain
        there as a witness against the people of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I know how rebellious and stubborn you are. Even now, while I
        am still alive and am here with you, you have rebelled against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        How much more rebellious will you be after my death!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow summon all the elders and officials of your tribes, so
        that I can speak to them directly and call heaven and earth to witness against
        them. "
      comments: []
    - title: The Song of Moses
      content: "I know that after my death you will become utterly corrupt and will
        turn from the way I have commanded you to follow. In the days to come, disaster
        will come down on you, for you will do what is evil in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        sight, making him very angry with your actions.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CListen, O heavens, and I will speak!Hear, O earth, the words
        that I say!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let my teaching fall on you like rain;let my speech settle like dew.Let
        my words fall like rain on tender grass,like gentle showers on young plants.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will proclaim the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;how glorious
        is our God!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He is the Rock; his deeds are perfect.Everything he does is just
        and fair.He is a faithful God who does no wrong;how just and upright he is!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut they have acted corruptly toward him;when they act so perversely,are
        they really his children?[[COMMENT(0)]]They are a deceitful and twisted generation.  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:5 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: "Is this the way you repay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,you foolish
        and senseless people?Isn\u2019t he your Father who created you?Has he not
        made you and established you?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember the days of long ago;think about the generations past.Ask
        your father, and he will inform you.Inquire of your elders, and they will
        tell you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the Most High assigned lands to the nations,when he divided
        up the human race,he established the boundaries of the peoplesaccording to
        the number in his heavenly court.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:8 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls, which read <b>the number of the sons of
          God, </b>and Greek version, which reads <b>the number of the angels of
          God; </b>Masoretic Text reads <b>the number of the sons of Israel.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor the people of Israel belong to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;Jacob
        is his special possession.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He found them in a desert land,in an empty, howling wasteland.He
        surrounded them and watched over them;he guarded them as he would guard his
        own eyes.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>as the pupil of his eye.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Like an eagle that rouses her chicksand hovers over her young,so
        he spread his wings to take them upand carried them safely on his pinions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> alone guided them;they followed no
        foreign gods.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He let them ride over the highlandsand feast on the crops of the
        fields.He nourished them with honey from the rockand olive oil from the stony
        ground.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He fed them yogurt from the herdand milk from the flock,together
        with the fat of lambs.He gave them choice rams from Bashan, and goats,together
        with the choicest wheat.You drank the finest wine,made from the juice of
        grapes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] soon became fat and unruly;the people
        grew heavy, plump, and stuffed!Then they abandoned the God who had made them;they
        made light of the Rock of their salvation.  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jeshurun, </b>a term of endearment for Israel.
    - title: 
      content: 'They stirred up his jealousy by worshiping foreign gods;they provoked
        his fury with detestable deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They offered sacrifices to demons, which are not God,to gods they
        had not known before,to new gods only recently arrived,to gods their ancestors
        had never feared.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You neglected the Rock who had fathered you;you forgot the God who
        had given you birth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saw this and drew back,provoked
        to anger by his own sons and daughters.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said, \u2018I will abandon them;then see what becomes of them.For
        they are a twisted generation,children without integrity.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have roused my jealousy by worshiping things that are not God;they
        have provoked my anger with their useless idols.Now I will rouse their jealousy
        through people who are not even a people;I will provoke their anger through
        the foolish Gentiles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For my anger blazes forth like fireand burns to the depths of the
        grave.[[COMMENT(0)]]It devours the earth and all its cropsand ignites the
        foundations of the mountains.  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:22 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I will heap disasters upon themand shoot them down with my arrows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will weaken them with famine,burning fever, and deadly disease.I
        will send the fangs of wild beastsand poisonous snakes that glide in the
        dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Outside, the sword will bring death,and inside, terror will strikeboth
        young men and young women,both infants and the aged.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I would have annihilated them,wiping out even the memory of them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I feared the taunt of Israel\u2019s enemy,who might misunderstand
        and say,\u201COur own power has triumphed!The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had nothing to do with this!\u201D\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut Israel is a senseless nation;the people are foolish, without
        understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, that they were wise and could understand this!Oh, that they might
        know their fate!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How could one person chase a thousand of them,and two people put
        ten thousand to flight,unless their Rock had sold them,unless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had given them up?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the rock of our enemies is not like our Rock,as even they recognize.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:31 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain. Greek version reads <b>our
          enemies are fools.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Their vine grows from the vine of Sodom,from the vineyards of Gomorrah.Their
        grapes are poison,and their clusters are bitter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their wine is the venom of serpents,the deadly poison of cobras.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u2018Am I not storing
        up these things,sealing them away in my treasury?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will take revenge; I will pay them back.In due time their feet
        will slip.Their day of disaster will arrive,and their destiny will overtake
        them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIndeed, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give justice to
        his people,and he will change his mind about[[COMMENT(0)]] his servants,when
        he sees their strength is goneand no one is left, slave or free.  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:36 '
        content: Or <b>will take revenge for.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then he will ask, \u2018Where are their gods,the rocks they fled
        to for refuge?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Where now are those gods,who ate the fat of their sacrificesand drank
        the wine of their offerings?Let those gods arise and help you!Let them provide
        you with shelter!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look now; I myself am he!There is no other god but me!I am the one
        who kills and gives life;I am the one who wounds and heals;no one can be
        rescued from my powerful hand!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now I raise my hand to heavenand declare, \u201CAs surely as I live,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'when I sharpen my flashing swordand begin to carry out justice,I
        will take revenge on my enemiesand repay those who reject me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will make my arrows drunk with blood,and my sword will devour flesh\u2014the
        blood of the slaughtered and the captives,and the heads of the enemy leaders.\u201D\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRejoice with him, you heavens,and let all of God\u2019s angels
        worship him.[[COMMENT(0)]]Rejoice with his people, you Gentiles,and let all
        the angels be strengthened in him.[[COMMENT(1)]]For he will avenge the blood
        of his children[[COMMENT(2)]];he will take revenge against his enemies.He
        will repay those who hate him[[COMMENT(3)]]and cleanse his people\u2019s
        land.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '32:43a '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek version; Masoretic Text lacks the
          first two lines. Compare Heb 1:6.
      - number: '32:43b '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew text lacks this sentence. Compare Rom
          15:10.
      - number: '32:43c '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek version; Masoretic Text reads <b>his
          servants.</b>
      - number: '32:43d '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek version; Masoretic Text lacks this
          line.
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses came with Joshua[[COMMENT(0)]] son of Nun and recited all
        the words of this song to the people.  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:44 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Hoshea, </b>a variant name for Joshua.
    - title: 
      content: 'When Moses had finished reciting all these words to the people of
        Israel, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "he added: \u201CTake to heart all the words of warning I have given
        you today. Pass them on as a command to your children so they will obey every
        word of these instructions. "
      comments: []
    - title: "Moses\u2019 Death Foretold"
      content: "These instructions are not empty words\u2014they are your life! By
        obeying them you will enjoy a long life in the land you will occupy when
        you cross the Jordan River.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That same day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo to Moab, to the mountains east of the river,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and climb Mount Nebo, which is across from Jericho. Look out across the land
        of Canaan, the land I am giving to the people of Israel as their own special
        possession. "
      comments:
      - number: '32:49 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the mountains of Abarim.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you will die there on the mountain. You will join your ancestors,
        just as Aaron, your brother, died on Mount Hor and joined his ancestors. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For both of you betrayed me with the Israelites at the waters of
        Meribah at Kadesh[[COMMENT(0)]] in the wilderness of Zin. You failed to demonstrate
        my holiness to the people of Israel there. '
      comments:
      - number: '32:51 '
        content: Hebrew <b>waters of Meribath-kadesh.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: Moses Blesses the People
      content: '  This is the blessing that Moses, the man of God, gave to the people
        of Israel before his death:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came from Mount Sinaiand dawned
        upon us[[COMMENT(0)]] from Mount Seir;he shone forth from Mount Paranand
        came from Meribah-kadeshwith flaming fire at his right hand.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:2a '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads <b>upon them.</b>
      - number: '33:2b '
        content: Or <b>came from myriads of holy ones, from the south, from his mountain
          slopes. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'Indeed, he loves his people;[[COMMENT(0)]]all his holy ones are in
        his hands.They follow in his stepsand accept his teaching.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:3 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>Indeed, lover of the peoples.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Moses gave us the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s instruction,the
        special possession of the people of Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:4 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>of Jacob. </b>The names \u201CJacob\u201D and \u201CIsrael\u201D
          are often interchanged throughout the Old Testament, referring sometimes
          to the individual patriarch and sometimes to the nation."
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> became king in Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014when
        the leaders of the people assembled,when the tribes of Israel gathered as
        one.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Jeshurun, </b>a term of endearment for Israel.
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribe of Reuben:[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CLet
        the tribe of Reuben live and not die out,though they are few in number.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:6 '
        content: Hebrew lacks <b>Moses said this about the tribe of Reuben.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribe of Judah:\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        hear the cry of Judahand bring them together as a people.Give them strength
        to defend their cause;help them against their enemies!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribe of Levi:\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you have given your Thummim and Urim\u2014the sacred lots\u2014to your faithful
        servants the Levites.[[COMMENT(0)]]You put them to the test at Massahand
        struggled with them at the waters of Meribah.  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:8 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew lacks <b>the Levites.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The Levites obeyed your wordand guarded your covenant.They were more
        loyal to youthan to their own parents.They ignored their relativesand did
        not acknowledge their own children.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They teach your regulations to Jacob;they give your instructions
        to Israel.They present incense before youand offer whole burnt offerings
        on the altar.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Bless the ministry of the Levites, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        accept all the work of their hands.Hit their enemies where it hurts the most;strike
        down their foes so they never rise again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribe of Benjamin:\u201CThe people of Benjamin
        are loved by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and live in safety beside him.He
        surrounds them continuouslyand preserves them from every harm.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribes of Joseph:\u201CMay their land be
        blessed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>with the precious gift of dew from
        the heavensand water from beneath the earth;  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'with the rich fruit that grows in the sun,and the rich harvest produced
        each month;  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'with the finest crops of the ancient mountains,and the abundance
        from the everlasting hills;  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "with the best gifts of the earth and its bounty,and the favor of
        the one who appeared in the burning bush.May these blessings rest on Joseph\u2019s
        head,crowning the brow of the prince among his brothers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Joseph has the majesty of a young bull;he has the horns of a wild
        ox.He will gore distant nations,even to the ends of the earth.This is my
        blessing for the multitudes of Ephraimand the thousands of Manasseh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribes of Zebulun and Issachar[[COMMENT(0)]]:\u201CMay
        the people of Zebulun prosper in their travels.May the people of Issachar
        prosper at home in their tents.  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:18 '
        content: Hebrew lacks <b>and Issachar.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "They summon the people to the mountainto offer proper sacrifices
        there.They benefit from the riches of the seaand the hidden treasures in
        the sand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribe of Gad:\u201CBlessed is the one who
        enlarges Gad\u2019s territory!Gad is poised there like a lionto tear off
        an arm or a head.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Gad took the best land for themselves;a leader\u2019s
        share was assigned to them.When the leaders of the people were assembled,they
        carried out the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s justiceand obeyed his
        regulations for Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribe of Dan:\u201CDan is a lion\u2019s
        cub,leaping out from Bashan.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribe of Naphtali:\u201CO Naphtali, you
        are rich in favorand full of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s blessings;may
        you possess the west and the south.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses said this about the tribe of Asher:\u201CMay Asher be blessed
        above other sons;may he be esteemed by his brothers;may he bathe his feet
        in olive oil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May the bolts of your gates be of iron and bronze;may you be secure
        all your days.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThere is no one like the God of Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]He rides
        across the heavens to help you,across the skies in majestic splendor.  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:26 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Jeshurun, </b>a term of endearment for Israel.
    - title: 
      content: "The eternal God is your refuge,and his everlasting arms are under
        you.He drives out the enemy before you;he cries out, \u2018Destroy them!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Israel will live in safety,prosperous Jacob in security,in a land
        of grain and new wine,while the heavens drop down dew.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Death of Moses
      content: '  Then Moses went up to Mount Nebo from the plains of Moab and climbed
        Pisgah Peak, which is across from Jericho. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        showed him the whole land, from Gilead as far as Dan; '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'all the land of Naphtali; the land of Ephraim and Manasseh; all the
        land of Judah, extending to the Mediterranean Sea[[COMMENT(0)]]; '
      comments:
      - number: '34:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the western sea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "the Negev; the Jordan Valley with Jericho\u2014the city of palms\u2014as
        far as Zoar. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CThis is
        the land I promised on oath to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob when I said, \u2018I
        will give it to your descendants.\u2019 I have now allowed you to see it
        with your own eyes, but you will not enter the land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses, the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, died there
        in the land of Moab, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had said. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> buried him[[COMMENT(0)]] in a valley
        near Beth-peor in Moab, but to this day no one knows the exact place. '
      comments:
      - number: '34:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>He buried him; </b>Samaritan Pentateuch and some Greek
          manuscripts read <b>They buried him.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Moses was 120 years old when he died, yet his eyesight was clear,
        and he was as strong as ever. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people of Israel mourned for Moses on the plains of Moab for
        thirty days, until the customary period of mourning was over.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now Joshua son of Nun was full of the spirit of wisdom, for Moses
        had laid his hands on him. So the people of Israel obeyed him, doing just
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There has never been another prophet in Israel like Moses, whom the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> knew face to face. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent him to perform all the miraculous
        signs and wonders in the land of Egypt against Pharaoh, and all his servants,
        and his entire land. '
      comments: []
